title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind 10 cups of zucchini in meat grinder, along with onions, peppers and salt.
Mix and let set overnight.
Next day, drain in colander and rinse in cold water.
Add vinegar, mustard, celery, turmeric, cornstarch and black pepper.
Mix and cook 3 minutes (simmer).
Stir as it sticks on easily.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together; make into cakes and fry as you would pancakes, etc.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by small spoonfuls into hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: shepherds pie
directions: Mix hamburger meat, onion and soup.
Put 1/2 of the potatoes in a casserole dish.
Add hamburger mixture.
Cover with cheese. Add the remaining potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Sift flour, soda, spices, milk, sherry, nuts and fruit.
Flour nuts and fruit with part of flour.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.
My kids love this.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix jello and boiling water, then cool.
Mix enough jello mixture to cream cheese and sugar to blend.
Whip Carnation milk; add all ingredients.
Layer a long Pyrex dish with graham crackers and fill with mixture.
Chill before serving.
Freezes well.

title: cornish game hen (with wild rice)
directions: Wash game hens.
Sprinkle with salt (including the inside of cavity as well as entire outside of bird).
Prepare rice according to directions on the box.
When rice is done, add raisins and mix together.
Stuff each hen with mixture and wrap in foil or place in roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Baste each bird with melted butter.
Leave in oven until golden brown and tender, usually 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt chocolate over hot, not boiling, water.
Combine with oil.
Drizzle this combination over the Orange Frosting.
Smear it a little with a spatula.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until light and creamy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla; continue beating.
Lastly, add shredded zucchini and well drained pineapple.

title: scalloped ham and potatoes
directions: Soak the sliced raw potatoes in cold water for 1 hour and then drain and dry thoroughly with a towel.

Next melt the fat, add the flour and cook until bubbling; then add the milk gradually, stirring constantly, and cook until smooth and slightly thickened. Place in a greased casserole a layer of potatoes, using one third of them.
Over these slice one onion and sprinkle with pepper.
Lay on these the pieces of ham, then repeat with potatoes and onion. Salt and pour the white sauce over all and bake for one hour in a 350° oven.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar, butter and egg in a saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Cool until thick enough to spread, beating occasionally.

title: strawberries savannah
directions: In medium mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Gradually add flour and sugar
alternately with milk and water, beating with electric mixer until smooth.
Beat inmelted butter.
Refrigerate batter at least 1 hour.
Make 20-25 crepes.

title: carol's kolbassi casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, mix pineapple, chili sauce and brown sugar.
Then add kolbassi and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: far east celery
directions: Cook celery in small amount of water until tender-crisp (about 4 minutes).
Drain thoroughly and combine with next 4 ingredients. Place in buttered casserole.
Toss bread crumbs with oleo and almonds and sprinkle this over celery mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add beef, onion and garlic powder.
Mix well, then add sour cream.
Chill one hour.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix oleo, peanut butter and powdered sugar thoroughly.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Chill.
Melt chocolate bars and bits with paraffin together over hot water.
Dip balls (3/4 of the way) and place on waxed paper.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°, then cut down to 350° to bake.
Mix together all ingredients and bake in unbaked pie shell for 35 minutes.
Top of pie should be a golden brown.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Bring sugar, water and salt to hard boiled stage.
Place marshmallow cream in large bowl and stir in syrup.
Continue stirring until mixture is slightly stiff and forms peaks.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: coconut-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and Crisco.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add coconut, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts (if desired).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chalupas
directions: Place all ingredients in large pan.
Cover with water.
Cook 9-12 hours at low after reaching boiling point.

title: fried pork chop adobo
directions: Place oil in frying pan and heat up.
Fry sliced pork chop until close to browned.
Add garlic and onion into pan.
Fry until browned.
Add vinegar and pepper, simmer until almost dried out. Add soy sauce and stir.
Simmer until soy sauce is almost dried out.

title: meat balls
directions: Chop celery fine; add pepper, onion and rest of the ingredients.
Make into balls and pour sauce over balls.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peggy's escalloped corn
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, combine creamed corn, beaten eggs and milk.
Mix well. Add 1/2 of the crushed crackers and mix thoroughly.
Place remaining crushed crackers on top and smooth. Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until well browned.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix and beat well.
Pour over hot baked crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until it looks like coconut.
Cook and cut into squares.

title: mother's icebox rolls
directions: Proof the yeast by dissolving it in the lukewarm water and adding the pinch of sugar.
If it foams, it's active and ready. Mix the boiling water with the sugar, salt and shortening in a large mixing bowl.
Let cool to lukewarm and add the yeast mixture and beaten egg.
Gradually stir in the flour until well blended. Do not knead.
Turn into a large, greased bowl; cover with a damp cloth and refrigerate overnight or for at least 4 hours.

title: shrimp spread(great appetizer for parties!)
directions: Allow cream cheese to reach room temperature.
In a small bowl mix cream cheese by hand with onions and Worcestershire sauce. Spread mixture on large platter (12 to 14 inch diameter).
Mix cocktail sauce with chili sauce.
Pour/spread half the sauce on top of the cheese.
Place the shrimp on next and follow with the remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with parsley and keep refrigerated until your guests arrive.
Serve with crackers.

title: dirt cake
directions: Roll cookies fine.
Soften cream cheese and add sugar.
Make pudding with milk and combine with cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Put crushed cookies on the bottom and then Cool Whip mixture.
Layer in container and finish with cookies.
Put artificial flowers in it.
Make in 1 large flowerpot, yields 17 to 18 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour 1/2 batter into well-greased pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Pour on rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Combine all the other stuff and chill.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 pan.
Melt caramels with 1/3 milk, stirring occasionally.
Melt butter and add cake mix and 1/3 c. milk.
Stir until moist.
Spread 1/2 of dough on bottom of pan. Bake 6 minutes at 350 degrees.
Take out; sprinkle with chocolate chips and drizzle caramel over top.
Crumble rest of cake mix over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15-18 minutes or until you shake the pan and it does not move too much.
Cool, cut into bars and refrigerate.

title: smacking barbecue sauce
directions: Put in jar the onion, garlic, celery, parsley and half the tomatoes.
Cover the jar.
Press the Mix button and blend for 30 seconds.

title: tupperware sweet roll dough(all you do is measure.  dough makes itself.)
directions: Using very large Tupperware bowl, layer flour, salt, sugar, milk, water, eggs and yeast.
Do not stir!
Seal bowl and burp lid.
Let sit 30 to 45 minutes or until seal breaks.
Add 1 cup melted butter and stir until mixed.
Seal again and burp.
Let rise until double in size or the seal is broken (30 to 45 minutes).
Pour dough onto heavily floured surface and knead until smooth.
(Last step is easier to do 1/4 of the dough at a time.) Shape as desired.
Bake at 375°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt over medium heat until boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes without stirring.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir into popcorn on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and crack with spoon.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix eggs and oil in until moistened. Add pineapple and eggs together.
Mix well; add nuts, vanilla and bananas last.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: nachos casserole no. 1
directions: Combine taco sauce and chilies in a small bowl; set aside. Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a large skillet over medium-high heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Add 1 cup cheese, beans, 1/2 taco sauce mixture, water and cumin.

title: italian cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 325° to 350°.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.
Ice as desired.

title: mile high lemon pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cornstarch, flour, sugar and salt. Mix well.
Gradually add 2 cups water and stir until smooth. Bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir some hot mixture into egg yolks and return this to rest of hot mixture.
Return to heat, cook on low for 5 minutes.
Remove, gently stir in lemon juice, peel and butter. Pour into pie shell.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° long enough to bubble.

title: charmin cherry bars
directions: Sift together 1 cup flour and powdered sugar; cut in butter until coarse.
Press into a 9 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients. Add eggs; stir in cherries, coconut and pecans.
Spread over partially cooked crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix.
Pour into baked pie shell and set aside.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until creamy. Combine flour until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces.
Drop by rounded spoonful onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Remove skin from all chicken parts except the wings.
Place in roasting pan or dish.
Add apricot jelly to each piece.
Spread soup mix over all chicken parts.
Cover all with dressing, salt and pepper.
Cook for 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels in microwave but do not let burn.
Add whipping cream and mix well.
Add pecans and mix well.
Butter a cookie sheet and drop caramel mixture onto cookie sheet by the teaspoon full.
Put turtles in freezer and freeze.
Melt chocolate almond bark and dip turtles until coated well.
Drop on wax paper to let dry.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Beat together the
Bisquick, milk, eggs and salt until smooth. Stir in broccoli and cheese. Pour into buttered 1/2-quart dish. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: chunky beef and bean stew
directions: About 3 1/2 hours before serving:
rinse beans.
Heat beans in 4 cups water to boiling; cool 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain and rinse beans; set aside.
In hot oil, cook beef for stew until well browned on all sides.
In drippings over medium heat, cook onion until tender, stirring. Add meat, beans, carrots and remaining ingredients; add 3 cups water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours until meat and beans are tender, stirring occasionally. Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: layered ham casserole
directions: In casserole, layer as follows:
ham pieces, sliced potatoes, sliced onions, soup, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers if necessary. Top casserole with grated cheese.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until hot and bubbly!!

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and bell peppers in skillet.
Drain hamburger.
In bowl, mix first 8 ingredients.
In medium skillet, pour 1/2 cornbread mixture.
Add hamburger and cheese.
Cover with remainder of cornbread mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: diet chicken
directions: Saute the carrots, onion and green pepper in water.
Let water boil down until mixture browns slightly.
Add the remaining ingredients, except pineapple chunks.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
The pineapple chunks may be added the last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Slice chicken breasts in thin slices and fry in skillet in cooking oil until brown.
Add green peppers and onion, cut up; stir-fry with chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon stir-fry ingredients onto tortillas.
Add cheese, lettuce and tomato and top with sour cream.
Fold over and eat.

title: easy banana salad
directions: Arrange banana slices on individual lettuce leaves.
Mix mayo, lemon juice and peanuts.
Top bananas with mayo mixture.

title: mushrooms and rice
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients (pretzels, butter and sugar). Press into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes. Whip together next 3 ingredients (cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar).
Spread over cooled pretzel mixture.
Combine last 4 ingredients.
Chill; when mixture thickens pour over cooled mixture and chill.
Nuts and Cool Whip may be used for topping.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen and baked a trifle longer when getting ready to serve.
Equally good cold.
Makes 70 balls.

title: chocolate coffee punch
directions: Mix coffee, sugar, syrup, vanilla and hot water.
Cool.
Add 1 quart milk and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add 1 quart milk and the half and half.
Pour over the ice cream (break up into pieces). Makes 1 gallon (20 cups served).

title: ice ring
directions: Arrange mandarin sections, washed mandarin leaves and washed mint leaves in the bottom of mold.
Put in enough water to barely cover mandarin sections.
Freeze.
When thoroughly frozen add enough water to fill mold.
Freeze.
Unmold, place in punch bowl fruit side up.
Use as decorative ice ring in punch or tea.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Beat egg yolks with milk.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, until the consistency of pie crust.
Turn out onto floured surface and roll out until thin.
Dust with flour on each side and place on waxed paper.
Let dry for 2 to 4 hours.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease two 8-inch round cake pans.
In each pan combine 1/4 cup melted butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar. Flatten with fork.
Place 5 pineapple rings in each pan and put a cherry in the center of each ring.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour 1/2 of batter over pineapple and cherries in each pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn out on plates before cooling.

title: brandied peaches
directions: Drain peaches thoroughly and reserve syrup.
Boil all peach syrup in a saucepan until it is reduced to less than a cup, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in brandy.
Pack drained peaches into wide-mouthed 1 1/2-pint jar.
Add brandy mixture to fill jar.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate.
Allow to mellow at least overnight before serving.
Will keep much longer in the refrigerator.

title: audrey's easy casserole
directions: Mix all above ingredients with 1 cup salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Spread in flat casserole and cover with Chinese noodles.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot.

title: perfect seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve on crisp lettuce leaves or use as a sandwich filler.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown all sides of stew meat.
Place in a 5-quart pot that is filled with 3 quarts of water.
Let meat cook for 1 hour for tenderness.
Add tomatoes, corn, onion, potatoes, okra, salt, pepper, sugar, lemon pepper and carrots.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Then, add spaghetti noodles; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add thawed broccoli.
Cook together for a few minutes.	Add rice, mushroom soup and cheese.
Mix well; place in a buttered baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: superb peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup.
Cook until mixture spins thread.
Add peanuts; cook until golden brown.
Remove from heat. Add soda; stir well.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
When cool, break and store in airtight container.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and half of flour; mix well.
Add oil and remaining flour.
Mix until smooth; knead. Place in a greased glass bowl.
Cover and let rise 2 hours (oil top first).
Put on a floured surface and knead in more flour.
Shape rolls and put in a greased muffin pan.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400°.

title: pork pie
directions: Brown pork and hamburg with a bit of butter in frying pan.
Add seasonings.
Boil and dice potatoes into very tiny pieces.
Simmer potatoes and meat blend.
Bake pie in 400° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is browned.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 4 minutes.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour in greased cake pan.
Cool before serving.

title: newfangled green bean casserole
directions: Working with half of the beans at a time, cook in boiling salted water, stirring often, 4 to 5 minutes until bright green and crisp-tender. Remove with tongs to bowl of ice water. Drain well on paper towels. (Can be made 2 days ahead. Wrap in paper towels and place in plastic food storage bag; refrigerate.)

title: rice casserole(serves 8)
directions: In large bowl combine the last 5 ingredients.
Add rice, broccoli and cheese.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients, using high altitude flour additions for cake mix.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked asparagus
directions: Cook and drain asparagus.
Combine and slowly heat soup and milk.
In 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer asparagus and soup mixture.
Top with Parmesan or crackers if you wish.

title: hot cheese toast
directions: Cook bacon by placing it on a rack over a shallow pan and baking at 350° for about 20 minutes or until crisp.
Drain on paper towels and set aside.
Combine all ingredients except bread and paprika in a bowl.
Crumble bacon and add to mixture; set aside.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken thighs about 45 minutes until done.
Debone and chop chicken.
Cook ground beef, and add all other ingredients. Add Rotel tomatoes and the hot catsup to individual taste.
Let simmer 20 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O
in 1 cup hot water.
Add 3/4 cup cold water, crushed
pineapple,
fruit
cocktail and pecans.
Pour into square pan.
Let set until jelled.	Cover with Cool Whip.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done but not mushy.
Cool, peel and shred into a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat milk, whipping cream, dry mustard, salt, nutmeg and cheese until cheese is melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Dot with butter.
Cool; refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Do not cover during baking.
Serves 8.

title: cucumber sauce
directions: Wash cucumber thoroughly if waxed.
Shred unpeeled cucumber and press to remove excess water.
Whip cream until stiff.
Add cucumber, salt, hot pepper sauce and lemon juice. Stir to mix well.
Make about 1 1/2 cups.
Serve with fish in lieu of tartar. Makes a great dip also with raw veggies.

title: tang pie
directions: In a large bowl, place Eagle Brand milk, cream cheese and Tang.
Beat until blended and fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in graham cracker crust and chill.
Garnish with mandarin orange slices.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Cut up head of cauliflower.
Cut up pieces of butter and put over cauliflower.
Add 1 cup shredded cheese.
Top with Ritz crackers, sprinkled with butter.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: lovely lemon cheese cake
directions: For a no-mess way to make crumbs, crush in plastic bag using rolling pin to crush.

title: sweet-and-sour spareribs
directions: Place ribs on a rack in a large, shallow roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chinese oriental pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles.
Stir until well blended; top with the Chinese noodles.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: pasta primavera with a twist
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese, garlic powder and pepper.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Add chicken.
Heat through, stirring often.
Serve over macaroni.
Toss before serving.
Serves 4.

title: black and white cupcakes
directions: Beat smooth the cream cheese, egg and 1/3 cup sugar.
Add chocolate chips and set aside.
In separate bowl, beat until smooth all remaining ingredients.
Fill cupcake tins 1/2 full of chocolate mixture.
Drop 1 tablespoon cream cheese mix in center of each.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14.

title: marshmallow puffs
directions: Line a 9 inch square pan with foil.
Spray pan.
Arrange marshmallows. Melt chips, peanut butter and butter.
Pour over marshmallows.
Cut in between marshmallows to serve.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix well.
Stir in 1 cup of cream.
Cook until thick.
Flavor with vanilla.

title: superb crab spread
directions: Using electric mixer or food processor, combine cream cheese and mayonnaise until creamy.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Serve with crackers or vegetables.
Yields 2 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour in pie crust and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until slightly set in center.
Be sure not to overbake.
Let pie cool before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: low calorie strawberry pie and crust
directions: Cut berries up and sprinkle with sweetener.
Heat water with cornstarch and salt, stirring until thickened.
Stir in Jell-O and seasonings.
Cool a bit.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch pie plate or Low Calorie Pie Crust.
Chill.
Top with frozen whipped topping if desired.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package; drain, set aside.
Heat soup with milk.
Mix drained tuna, soup, mayonnaise and onion in Pam sprayed 2-quart baking dish.
Salt/pepper to taste.
Add drained noodles and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 425° approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream soup of choice

title: cherry punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add water, lemon juice and pour over cracked ice.
Add ginger ale last.
Serves 12.

title: pie shell
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Mix in oil well and then water. Knead dough for 15 minutes.
Flour pastry sheet and roll dough out as desired.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.

title: bubbly holiday punch
directions: Chill pineapple juice and sparkling apple juice.
Combine undrained pineapple, fruit and mint in 6 cup mold.
Add enough juice or water to fill.
Freeze.
Combine punch ingredients in bowl.
Float ice mold.

title: cheesy rotini
directions: Prepare noodles as directed; drain.
In large skillet, cook ground beef, green pepper and onion over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add tomatoes, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk, Ricotta cheese and rotini noodles.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus parmesan
directions: Wash asparagus.
Put into a small amount of boiling salted water in a skillet.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook 5 minutes, uncovered. Cover and cook an additional 10 minutes or until just tender.
Pour melted butter into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put cooked asparagus into casserole and sprinkle with mixture of cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: little party pizza
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef. Drain grease. Add cheese and melt. Add slices and let cool. Spread on small slices of rye bread. Good to freeze for later use.

title: 8 minute cheese cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with mixer on medium until very fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon into crust.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: friendship salad
directions: Rub dish with oil. Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add the softened cream cheese and stir until completely dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and congeal. Easy to divide into two smaller salads.
May be used as a dessert or salad.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and pour into 9x13 pan.
Mix together 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup chopped pecans; sprinkle over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix gently in large casserole dish.
Cover with pie crust and prick few times with fork.
Bake at 350° until brown (15 to 20 minutes).

title: steak with onions and peppers
directions: Cook onions, bell peppers, tomato juice, lemon peel, paprika and garlic in 10-inch skillet over medium heat 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium-low. Stir in broth. Cover and cook about 10 minutes or until liquid has almost evaporated.
Stir in basil, lemon juice and salt.
Keep warm.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Add cocoa to sugar and mix well.
Stir in 2 cups milk to make smooth mixture.
Cook over medium heat.
Beat egg yolks.
Add cornstarch and 1/4 cup milk to make smooth blend.
Add salt and stir into cocoa/sugar mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made of egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 375° until meringue is lightly brown.
Cool 2 to 4 hours prior to serving.

title: grandma sayle's hard gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If needed, add enough flour to make a dough like baking powder biscuit dough.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (8 x 8-inch) pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ham glaze
directions: Combine sugar, cloves and pineapple.
Remove ham 30 minutes before baking ends.
Score top of ham in crisscross pattern.
Coat ham with glaze.
Return to oven.
Baste ham with balance of glaze every 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill evaporated milk.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ice cubes to thicken jello.
Add lemon juice and sugar to jello. Whip evaporated milk until thick (peaks easily when spoon is used to make a peak).
Fold milk into jello mixture.
Pour into a large Pyrex dish (11 x 14-inch) to which vanilla wafer crumbs have been put on bottom.
Sprinkle top with remaining vanilla wafers. Chill.

title: dill slaw
directions: Finely grate cabbage.
Add onion.
Mix remaining ingredients for dressing.
Toss dressing with cabbage mixture.
Chill; garnish with tomatoes.

title: pickled veggies
directions: Put veggies or cucumbers in jars and add to each jar 1 Tbsp dill seed, 2 cloves garlic, and 7 peppercorns.
Combine vinegar, salt, and water and bring to a boil.
Fill jars with liquid 1/2 inch from the top.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into mixture.
Chill the dough 1/2 hour.
Roll chilled dough into balls the size of small walnuts.
Dip tops in sugar.
Place 3 inches apart onto cookie sheet, sugar side up. Sprinkle each cookie with a few drops of water.
This will crackle the top.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: diabetic nut cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except nut meats and orange rind.
Stir well.
Add nut meats and orange rind.
Drop by large teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onions and saute until golden and tender, stirring frequently.
Add salt and pepper, then meat stock; stir until mixture bubbles.
Spoon into four crocks or small casserole dishes.
Top with toasted bread. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella or Swiss cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Use oxtail or neck bones for meat stock.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Preheat graham cracker crust. Mix Eagle Brand milk, egg yolk and lemon juice until fluffy. Stir in lemon rind. Pour into crust. Top with Cool Whip topping. Chill overnight.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir smooth.
Add pineapple, celery and pecans.
Stir until mixed. Refrigerate.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut recipe in half to make 7 to 8-inch square dish full.

title: dip
directions: Melt and blend well.
Serve hot with the regular Frito-Lay bite-size chips.

title: candied potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes.
Wash and slice in finger size pieces. Cook down oranges until tender.
Do not stir; shake pan.

title: triple celery bisque
directions: Blend one cup of love and one half cup of kindness.
Add alternately in small portions one cup of appreciation and 3 cups of pleasant companionship into which has been sifted three teaspoons of deserving praise.
Flavor with one teaspoon of carefully chosen advise.
Lightly fold in one cup of cheerfulness to which has been added a pinch of sorrow.
Pour with tender care into small, clean hearts and let bake until well matured.
Turn out on the surface of society.
Humbly invoke God's blessing and it will serve all mankind.

title: quail baked with honey
directions: Salt quail lightly and roll in flour, then brown lightly in melted butter. Remove to a casserole dish and cook the onion in butter until done but not brown. Sprinkle rosemary over each quail. Pour a teaspoon of honey over each one, then put the onions on top. Pour the can of undiluted chicken broth around quail. Cover and bake at 350° for 3/4 hour. Baste occasionally.

title: coconut chews
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and confectioners sugar. Blend in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press mixture in bottom of ungreased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread over hot baked layer.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
While warm, spread with orange-lemon icing.
Cool. Cut into bars.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Coat chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in olive oil (prefer electric skillet).
Remove from skillet.
Add Marsala, onions and mushrooms.
Cook down.
Add chicken and simmer, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and butter; add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt, baking powder and vanilla alternately with flour and milk.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Make enchilada sauce mix according to package directions using the 8 ounce can tomato sauce and water.
Meanwhile, heat 1/4 to 1/2-inch oil in small skillet.
Fry tortillas one at a time about 3 seconds on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Stuff tortilla with chicken and cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan with seam down. When all are stuffed, pour sauce over them, sprinkle with olives and then add layer of cheese.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dip chicken into 1/2 cup buttermilk, then roll chicken in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan, breast side down.
Bake 30 minutes uncovered.
Turn chicken and bake for 15 minutes more.
Turn chicken again and pour mixture of 1 cup buttermilk and mushroom soup over chicken, baking 15 minutes more. Remove chicken to platter and serve with pan gravy.
I have used crushed Ritz crackers instead of flour, and it gives a somewhat richer flavor.

title: light bread cobbler
directions: Line pan with fruit. Cut bread into cubes.
Melt butter.
Mix with sugar and eggs.
Pour over and bake at 325° until brown.

title: cheese soup
directions: Fix veggies according to package. Drain and chop. Fry onion in margarine. Add flour, salt and pepper to taste, then add milk and bring to a boil 1 minute.
Be careful not to let it burn. Add chicken broth, cheese, water, veggies and mustard.
Heat through and serve.

title: quick and easy pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl, and shortening, 1/2 c. milk, and eggs. Stir until flour is dampened, then beat 2 minutes. Pour into loaf pan, 4 by 13, and bake at 350 until done. The cake will be golden brown with a crack in top.

title: muscadine preserves
directions: Wash and pick over berries.
Pulp muscadines, placing hulls in one container and pulp in another.
Add water to hulls just to cover and cook slowly until tender.
Could be as much as an hour. Cook pulp slowly until seeds separate.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Being careful to save all juice, put pulp through colander to remove seeds.
Combine hulls with the water they were cooked in and the pulp and its juice, mixing well.
Mix liquid mixture cup for cup with sugar.
I usually use a Dutch oven that will hold 4 cups of each.
Bring liquid to boil before adding sugar.
Boil rapidly, skimming foam.
Test for doneness by placing about a teaspoon in saucer and placing it in freezer sections of refrigerator.
When it jells, remove mixture from fire.
Pour into jars.
Add paraffin and jar tops.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in spray bottle.
Spray on meat as it cooks.

title: apple salad
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl and stir in 3/4 cup Miracle Whip.
Serves 8.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat oil.
Cook chicken until brown on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir soup mix and water into skillet; cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: blackberry pudding
directions: Start water boiling.
Cream 1 cup sugar and butter together. Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk and mix well.
Pour batter into buttered pan (jelly roll pan), then pour blackberries on top.
Now sprinkle sugar on top and pour over 1 1/4 to 2 cups of water.
Bake in a 350° oven until top is golden brown, about 50 minutes.

title: curried salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Press into a greased loaf pan. Sprinkle with bread crumbs sauteed in butter with a little thyme or rosemary. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Serve with Curry Sauce.

title: luscious cheese cake
directions: Turn toast into crumbs.
Stir in powdered sugar and lemon peel or juice.
Using a fork or pastry blender, blend in butter or oleo, softened.
With fingers or back of spoon, press crumbs very firmly into pan and up on sides.
Set aside.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix the first four ingredients in a casserole dish, top with the margarine.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serves 5.

title: strawberry fig jelly
directions: Cook figs and sugar together until figs are very soft.
Add jello and Sure-Jell.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Stir well.
Pour in jars while hot to seal.

title: crusty oven baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking sheet.
Melt butter in saucepan; add garlic and saute for 10 seconds.
Remove from heat. Combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, thyme and pepper.
Dip chicken in butter; roll in bread crumb mixture to coat.
Drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake until chicken is lightly browned, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Cut Velveeta into chunks.
Place all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook on low 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until heated through.
Stir occasionally.

title: cranberry-orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into mold.
Chill until set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken on bottom of oblong baking dish.
Prepared stuffing on top.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and sour cream, pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Melt butter, sugar and syrup.
Add oatmeal and flour.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter. Spread on baked crust.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: red eye gravy
directions: Pour strong black coffee and water in skillet and stir to loosen all the brown particles from the bottom of the skillet. Bring to a full boil.
It's ready to serve!

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in order; top with 2 to 3 cups crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch buttered dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel snack mix
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Spray a large roasting pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Place butter in small sauce pan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour into a large mixing bowl and add yeast mixture, salt and eggs.
Add flour and mix well. Cover and refrigerate until time to use.
When ready to use punch down dough, roll out and place on a greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise in a warm place free from draft until double in bulk. About an hour.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown. Yield 4 dozen.

title: pork and mostaccioli special
directions: Boil mostaccioli 8 minutes (not overdone).
Saute pork (cut in strips) in olive oil and seasonings.
Remove from pan.
Put in capers and wine (red wine is okay).
Bring to boil.
Add more basil if desired.
Add defrosted peas (at least at room temperature).
Add fresh tomato, seeded and cut in pieces.
Put all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Nice one-dish meal.
Serves 4.

title: shortcut lasagna
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add meat; cook, breaking up with spoon. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and vegetable juice.

Cover bottom of oiled 13 x 9-inch baking dish with thin layer of meat sauce. Add layer of uncooked noodles, cottage and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, ending with meat sauce on top.
Cover tightly with heavy aluminum foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; let stand for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Cut into squares and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Add water to potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
Make white sauce with margarine, flour and milk.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add ham and undrained vegetables.
Heat; do not boil. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in skillet with butter.
Remove the chicken to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In the drippings, saute onion and celery until tender.
Add cranberry sauce and barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting every 15 minutes. Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: cornbread recipe
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Mix just until well blended.
Make in greased pan at 450° for 35 minutes or until light brown and cornbread leaves sides of pan.
(If using for dressing, make ahead of time and let cool.)

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon drained fruit over batter.
Mix sugar and juice and pour over the top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut up artichoke hearts and mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Don't over cook or the dip will separate.

title: dirt
directions: In small bowl, combine powdered sugar and cream cheese; cream thoroughly.
In large bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Beat and combine with ingredients in small bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In separate bowl, crush Oreo cookies.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Drain apricots, reserving 12 ounces juice.
Cut apricots into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and stir until sugar dissolves.
Fill 5 ounce paper cups 3/4 full; freeze.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Place chipped beef on bottom of baking dish.
Wrap each breast with strip of bacon and place on top of beef.
Mix the sour cream and soup together; pour over chicken.
Bake in oven, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.
Very good.
Serve with yellow rice.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 11 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover with Ritz crackers and drizzle with margarine or butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix pineapple, nuts, sugar and 1 cup coconut.
Do not drain. Let cool in refrigerator.
Take jello and 2 cups boiling water. Fold in strawberries.
Have a little icy.
Cool in refrigerator. Mix pineapple and jello mixture together.
Fold in 1 tub Cool Whip.
Break cake into bite-size pieces.
Start with cake and layer with mixture, ending with cake.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle remainder of coconut and nuts.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in brown paper bag and let stand 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to crackers in bag and shake.
Put on baking sheet and bake in warm oven for 15 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread in bottom of pan. Pour pinto beans on top of bread. Cut up celery, onions and peppers. Spread over top of beans.
Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice well and pour over top. No baking required.
Best when made the day before serving.

title: buche de noel -- christmas yule log
directions: Set oven at 400°f. 200°c. gas mark 6. Grease a shallow 11 x 16 pan, line with waxed paper.
Grease and lightly flour the paper. Sift together the flour, cocoa and cornstarch.
Beat the egg whites with salt until they hold soft peaks.
Beat in the sugar a tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until egg whites are very firm.
Break up the yolks with a fork, add vanilla.
Fold 1/4 of egg white mixture into the yolks.
Pour this on top of the remaining whites.
Sprinkle cocoa mixture on the top, fold gently together.
Do not over mix.
Spread evenly into the pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spray a 6-muffin pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into muffin pan and bake at 400° until done.

title: apple-cinnamon cup
directions: Dissolve gelatin and candy in boiling water.
Stir in applesauce, lemon juice and salt.
Chill to partially set.
Form cheese into tiny balls (a few minutes in the freezer makes this easier to do).
Fold cheese balls and nuts into mixture.
Spoon into muffin tins with paper bake cup liners.
Chill until set. Yields 15 (1/3-cup) molds.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; let cool and shred chicken.
Set aside.
Melt butter.
Add milk, then cornstarch and cook until it thickens. Add shredded chicken pieces.
Put in casserole dish.
Place rolls on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until buns/rolls are brown.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: In saucepan, bring pineapple to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add buttermilk and mix well. Cool to room temperature.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour in a 11 x 7-inch dish.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cut in squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: granny's 60 minute rolls
directions: Heat milk.
Sprinkle yeast over top of warm, not hot, milk and allow to dissolve.
Add shortening, eggs, sugar, salt and flour. Mix well.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Punch down and let rise another 15 minutes.
Shape into rolls and place in greased pan. Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until rolls are brown.
Brush tops with butter.

title: blushing pink dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Cut the chicken breasts into bite-size pieces.
Place the pieces in a shallow bowl.
Mix together half the soy sauce, sake and sugar, then add half the garlic and ginger with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over the chicken.
Cover and leave to marinate overnight.
Turn the chicken pieces in the marinade occasionally during the marinating time.
Thread the cubes of chicken onto oiled kebab skewers.
Brush with oil.
Barbecue or broil under moderate heat for about 10 minutes, until the chicken is tender.
Baste the chicken with the marinade and turn frequently during cooking.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Mix all ingredients together. Grease pie pan and pour in filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Makes its own crust!
Makes 2 pies.

title: white fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until boiling point, then cook 10 more minutes.
Take off stove and add jar of marshmallow cream and nuts. Place in greased pan.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: In a small bowl combine all ingredients.
Mix until crumbly. Remove pie from oven and increase temperature to 400°.
Sprinkle topping over filling.
Return pie to oven and bake for about 10 minutes more or until golden.

title: western dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and mix (puree) thoroughly.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix together
flour,
sugar
and
shortening.
Take out 1 1/2 cups for the topping.
After crumbs for topping has been taken out, beat the
eggs, cloves and buttermilk with the soda added, together with
the
rest
of
the
crumb mixture.
Beat well, pour batter
into
greased
pan
and
sprinkle the crumb topping over it.
Bake
at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: french bean and potato casserole
directions: Cook the potatoes and cream them. Brown the ground beef and drain. Drain the green beans and mix with the ground beef and tomato soup in a casserole dish. Spread the creamed potatoes over the top and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan, bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves, cool.
Pour mixture into large bowl, add the next four ingredients and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer several hours before serving (mixture should be slushy).
Pour into punch bowl and stir in chilled soda.
Yields approximately 2 1/2 gallons.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients with mixer.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well by hand or mixer.
Bake in two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: piggin-out cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and juice of oranges well (3 to 4 minutes); add oranges and nuts.
Grease 2 (8-inch) round or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: cajun barbecued shrimp
directions: Melt 1 cup butter in large pan or skillet.
Add onion and the next 8 ingredients.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add chicken broth and beer.
Cook 1 minute more.
Place unpeeled shrimp in large roaster or casserole pan.
Pour sauce over top. Bake in a 375° oven until done, approximately 20 minutes, stirring often.
Serve with hot cooked rice and sourdough French bread. (Dip bread into juices in pan ... wonderful!!)

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and put in a buttered 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan. Combine crushed Ritz crackers with melted butter or margarine and cover casserole with this mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corned beef stew
directions: Crumble corned beef.
Cut up
tomatoes into small pieces. Dice onion and peel and dice potatoes.
Drain peas.
Cook all ingredients together until potatoes are done.
Thicken and serve over bread slices.

title: quick pasta
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain.
Add cold water over the noodles to stop the cooking.
Put other ingredients with noodles; place in microwave for 4 minutes on High.
Stir after 2 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: In a large 3-quart heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook over medium-high heat until mixture reaches firm ball stage (244°), stirring occasionally.

Add butter and gradually add milk so that mixture does not stop boiling. Stirring constantly, cook rapidly to firm ball stage again. Remove from heat, add vanilla and pour mixture into a buttered 9-inch square baking pan without scraping the sides of the saucepan.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soups with Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Bring a cup of water to a boil, add rice and set aside.
Cook broccoli until tender. Saute onion and celery until tender, drain and add to soup mixture.
Drain broccoli and add to mixture, then add rice.
Stir very well and cover with paprika on top.
Put in a 350° oven and bake for 30 minutes.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until skins are easily removed.
Slice and place in a buttered dish.
On top of potatoes sprinkle cinnamon and slice margarine on top evenly.
In a saucepan mix orange juice, flour, dark syrup, sugar and water.
On medium heat, bring to a boil.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
When it comes out of the oven, cool slightly and add marshmallows.

title: cukes in sour cream
directions: Mix all together.
Good served with fish, shellfish or ham.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef until crumbly.
Drain.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in sauce.
Cook lasagna according to directions. Drain and separate.
In a baking pan, layer sauce, noodles and cheeses.
Continue layering with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, creaming well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating 3 minutes (medium speed).
Mix in vanilla; slice bananas and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Reserve 12 slices for garnish.
Mold grated chocolate and bananas into sugar mixture.
Turn into cooled baked pie shell.
Garnish with nuts and bananas.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Best served the same day it is made.
May top with Cool Whip.

title: cheese yule log
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except parsley and pimento.
Beat on low speed until smooth.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
On wax paper, shape mixture into 10 x 2-inch log.
Roll in parsley. Chill until serving time.
At serving time, garnish with pimento stars.
Serve as a spread on bread or crackers.

title: spanish potatoes
directions: Brown potatoes, onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add green olives, black olives and dried tomatoes.
Cook together for 5 to 10 minutes and serve.
Very tasty.
A good way to use up leftover potatoes.

title: jane headley's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: heavenly strawberries
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar, stirring gently.
Cover and let stand at room temperature at least 1 hour.
Beat whipping cream until foamy.
Add liqueur and almond extract, beating until soft peaks form.
Fold strawberries into whipped cream mixture. Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Serve immediately.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread in bottom of pan (I use 10-inch quiche pan).
Layer other ingredients as listed.

title: pickled vegetables
directions: Bring vinegar, water, salt, sugar and hot pepper to boil. Chop cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Mix vegetables; put into jar.
Pour hot vinegar over and seal.
Water bath for 10 minutes.

title: mexican luncheon casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes, macaroni, buttermilk or sour cream, sugar, chili powder and salt. Cover.
Cook 10 minutes on high and 15 to 20 minutes on simmer. Makes 8 servings.

title: pot roast
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven, place roast with vinegar.
Over medium heat, brown roast on both sides.
Add salt, mushroom soup, potatoes, carrots and onion.
Add pepper to taste.
Cover pan. Place in a 325° oven and cook until roast is very tender.
The gravy will be made and vegetables cooked by the time the roast is tender, about 4 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash the lentils.
Place in a kettle.
Add the carrot, potato, celery and leaves and onion.
Cover with water; cook slowly for 1/2 hour.
Check occasionally.
Water may have to be added.
After the 1/2 hour, add a little oil, garlic powder to taste and tomato sauce.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Check; it may need additional water.
The last 15 minutes, slice the hot dogs or sausage and add.
Just before serving, add a little salt to taste (no pepper).

title: m. l.'s cake
directions: Mix 2 eggs, butter and cake mix in bowl (will be stiff). Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and sugar and spread on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar.
A good last minute dessert.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until partially cooked.
Let them cool, then grate
them.
Mix with sour cream.
Combine cheese and margarine; melt.
Stir into potatoes and sour cream.
Place in greased casserole.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add melted butter.
Beat eggs.
Add the milk; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell (unbaked) and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: raised donuts
directions: Combine shortening and boiling water.
Stir until shortening is melted.
Combine eggs, sugar and salt and beat in cold water. Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine three mixtures.
Add to flour.
Mix well.
Cover and chill overnight in refrigerator. Roll and cut.
Place on trays to rise (about double).
Fry in hot oil.
Turn over.
Drain.
Add sugar, if desired.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cajun southern fried chicken
directions: Take chicken and coat by sprinkling with cayenne pepper.
Make it red.
Then douse with hot sauce.
Refrigerate for hours.
Dip chicken in milk, then dredge in flour until coated.
Place coated pieces of chicken in medium-high heated oil.
Cook in oil at medium-high for 5 minutes on both sides until slightly crusty. Lower heat to medium and cook until golden brown which should take 20 to 30 minutes depending.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.

title: pickled mango
directions: Slice mangos.
Boil sugar, vinegar and salt.
Let it cool. Add all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Cover and let stand for a day.
Jar and refrigerate.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Simmer margarine, cocoa, water and vanilla for a few seconds. In mixing bowl combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Add oleo mixture.
Beat in eggs and milk.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and 1/2 cup chopped nuts as for pie crust.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Remove and cool.
Beat cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on crust.

title: easy barbecue
directions: Brown ground
beef.
Drain fat off. Add all other ingredients. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: old-fashioned blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, nutmeg and baking powder and mix in a large bowl.
Combine eggs, milk and melted butter, oleo or oil and mix in bowl.
Add butter mixture to dry mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Dust blueberries with 1 tablespoon reserved flour; spoon together with batter.
Fill 2/3 full in muffin pans. (Spray muffin pans with Pam.)
You may sprinkle with 1/4 cup of almonds.
Bake in 400° oven, preheated for 15 minutes.
Yield: 15 to 18 muffins.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Prepare at least several hours before serving to allow flavors to mingle.

title: party rolls
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, buttermilk and salt in medium saucepan. Heat until shortening melts.
Remove from heat and add the 3/4 c. water.
Add potato flakes and mix in with a wire whisk. Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.

Combine buttermilk mixture, eggs, and half of the flour in large bowl; add the yeast mixture, beating with dough hook or beaters until smooth. Add remaining flour, a little at a time to make a soft dough.
If you have a dough hook on your mixer, beat dough for 7 minutes.
If you do not, turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead for 8 minutes or until smooth and elastic.

title: yummy sugar cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, combine the sugars, margarine, oil, eggs and vanilla. Mix well until creamy. Add the flour. Place dough in refrigerator to chill, then roll into small balls about 1-inch in diameter. Roll each ball in additional sugar and place on cookie sheet. Press with a fork to flatten. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: lil's buttermilk bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and raisins; beat well. Bake in bread pan for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of buttered 8x12 baking dish.
Top with cheese, then sausage.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day:
Dilute 1 can cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300 degrees.
May put Durkee dried onions on top for added flavor.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bring chicken breast to boil; pick off.
Put in bottom of pan. Mix cream of chicken and cream of celery together with chicken. On top, put stuffing, butter and milk.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Mix butter, sugar, juice and coconut well.
Form balls around cherries.
Roll in crumbs.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, egg and lemon extract.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to mixture.
Alternate with milk.
Add 1 pint of blueberries gently.

title: cracker sausage cake
directions: Put sausage, brown sugar and boiling water together. Break up and mix by hand; add remaining ingredients. Place in tube-shaped pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash pie
directions: Combine squash, sugar, salt and spices.
Blend in eggs, milk and butter.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: pinwheel biscuits
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk, all at once, and mix until dough follows fork around bowl.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Add eggs with oil. Stir until moistened. DO NOT BEAT. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas. Grease three 9-inch pans with butter. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Cool in pans.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat salad dressing, cake mix, eggs, water and cinnamon at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Make cream cheese frosting for top.

title: maple pudding
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water until tender. Drain thoroughly.
Combine eggs and maple syrup and blend well.
Stir in milk, nutmeg and salt, then rice and raisins.
Place ingredients in buttered casserole and bake in moderate 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix together pudding with milk.
Add 8 ounces of Cool Whip and 1 cup of powdered sugar.
Make 3 layers, starting with graham crackers for a crust.
Add pudding, graham crackers, pudding, graham crackers and top with chocolate icing.
Heat icing in microwave until thin.
Spread icing on top of cake.
Chill before serving.

title: marble brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as directed on package.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Blend in eggs. Pour over brownie mixture.
Cut through batter with knife for marble effect.
Sprinkle with chips.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until cream cheese mixture is lightly browned.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: how to make applesauce
directions: Wash, peel and cut the apples!
Take the seeds out!
Add sugar!
Stir it!
Put it on the stove!
Last, save some for everyone!!!!

title: french dressing
directions: Combine; mix in a large bowl.
Nina puts it all in blender on high.
It chops the chops the onion and garlic.
Can add a little red food coloring.
Refrigerate.
No preservatives.
Yield: about 3 1/2 cups.

title: spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Can also be used as a marinade.
Yields about 1 cup.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Let cranberries and sugar stand overnight, stirring a couple of times.
The next day add juice and rind of orange.
(I put pulp in.)
Get the white stuff off the orange.
Add crushed pineapple, chopped celery, pecans and juice.
Dissolve 2 packages gelatine as per package directions.
Mold, if desired.

title: orange carrot cake
directions: Combine vegetable oil and sugar.
Mix and add cinnamon, nutmeg and orange rind.
Separate yolks and egg whites; beat egg whites until foamy consistency.
Add one yolk at a time with equal parts of foamy egg white.
Add carrots and walnuts.
Sift together and mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with the orange juice.
Mix at high speed for 1 minute.
Pour batter into a greased and floured or nonstick 10-inch tube pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except stuffing.
Add 1/2 package of stuffing.
Save the rest to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in jelly roll pan in 375° oven (any pan will do). Mix crushed corn flakes, cheese and seasonings.
Dip sliced potatoes in butter, then in corn flake mixture.
Lay slices in pan in a single layer.
Bake 1/2 hour or until potato tops are crisp and potatoes are tender.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Mix shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add to wet mixture.
Mix well.
Roll flat and cut 3-inch circles, 2 for each cookie.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Cover beef with cold water.
Bring to boil.
Skim.
Add garlic and peppercorns; simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Last hour add carrots, onions and potatoes.
Last 1/2 hour add wedges of cabbage.
Serve with Onion Gravy.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight containers.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat yolk of egg; add sugar or substitute, diluted milk and flavoring.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Stir briskly, pour into glass and serve very cold.
Makes 1 serving.

title: chocolate raspberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
In a heavy medium saucepan, combine the chocolate, butter and coffee.
Cook over low heat, stirring until melted and smooth.
Remove the pan from the heat and cool for 15 minutes. Beat in the eggs.

title: cocoa pie(old-time chocolate pie)
directions: Blend cocoa, salt and flour with a little cold water (enough to make sticky).
Heat milk.
To well-beaten eggs, add sugar and cocoa mixture.
Add hot milk and cook until thick.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Peel and cut melon rind into small pieces, leaving a little red.
Soak in salt for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Drain and rinse until it doesn't taste salty.
Cover with sugar.
Shake to make sure each piece is covered.
Let stand overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients with squash.
Save enough stuffing mix to put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually blend in dry ingredients which have been blended together in a separate bowl.
Chill dough 3 hours.
Roll 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with floured cookie cutters (or use confectioners sugar instead of flour to roll out your dough). Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat slightly; add onion and garlic and cook until vegetables are tender.
Add flour to sour cream, then add bouillon cube which has been dissolved in the hot water.
Add the pepper and mix.
Add the soup to the meat mixture and heat.
Add the sour cream mixture to the meat and cook over medium heat until bubbly. Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Serve over noodles.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except peas, and put in large Pyrex dish.
Add peas 1 hour before done.
Cook at 275° for 5 hours.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook beef until brown.
Drain fat.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Cook until tender.
Add spaghetti sauce, pepperoni and cooked noodles.
Simmer 10 minutes.
In a large baking dish, layer sauce and cheese, beginning with sauce and ending with cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: steak supreme
directions: Brown steak pieces.
Add remainder of the ingredients and simmer until tender.

title: chicken and swiss
directions: Place chicken breasts in casserole baking dish.
Put a slice of Swiss cheese on top of each piece of chicken.
Mix soups with wine and pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix with margarine and put on top of soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry omelette
directions: Heat butter in omelette pan.
In a bowl, beat eggs.
Crush strawberries very slightly and mix with yogurt and honey.
When the butter stops sizzling, pour in eggs.
Tilt the pan to coat evenly.
Shake pan gently while lifting edges of omelette so uncooked eggs can run underneath.
As soon as it is set, spread strawberry mixture in the center.
Fold omelette.
Cook a minute longer.
Turn onto plate.
Garnish with fresh mint.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce in pieces and place in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over top like icing.
Top with cheese.
Garnish with bacon.

title: green beans
directions: Mix ingredients; pour over beans.
Cook 30 minutes after they come to hard boil.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats, water and butter until butter melts while stirring occasionally.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add brown sugar, sugar, eggs, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Mix, then bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat lightly.
Add onion, garlic and spices and finish browning.
Add tomatoes, water or beer and powdered milk and cook a minimum of 3 hours over low heat, stirring frequently.
Add beans 1 hour before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Grease and flour a large pan, 11 x 19-inch.
Mix and cook 1/2 of the cake batter for about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt the caramel, butter and milk in a double boiler or microwave.
When smooth, pour over finished cake.
Cover with a layer of pecans (I chop them, but you don't have to), then chocolate chips.
Cover with remaining cake mix and cook for 20 minutes or maybe a little longer.
It is done when an inserted toothpick comes out with only caramel on it.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg. Combine flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture, gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop rounded measuring tablespoon of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool for 2 minutes. Remove to cooling rack. Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Drain asparagus and set 3/4 cup of asparagus liquid aside.
Place asparagus in Pyrex dish.
Add layers of sliced Cheddar cheese and hard cooked eggs.
Mix 3/4 cup of asparagus liquid with can of soup.
Pour over layers in casserole dish and cover with cracker or bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: rabbit
directions: Wash and dry rabbit.
Roll in flour.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Brown rabbit.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is clear.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer until rabbit is very tender.
Thicken gravy with cornstarch.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: one-dish chicken bake
directions: In a bowl, toss stuffing mix and included seasoning packet with water.
Place chicken in a 2 qt. casserole dish; salt and pepper lightly.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over chicken.
Spoon stuffing evenly over top.
Bake uncovered at 375° for about 60 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Serves 4.
tags: cream of mushroom soup OR cream of chicken soup

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Add rice and 1 can of beef consomme, undiluted.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Use eggs, onions and green peppers according to amount of corned beef hash.
Make into patties like hamburger.
Brown until done.
Serve.

title: gouda cheese and puff pastry
directions: Center cheese in pastry.
Bring up sides and secure.
Place in pie pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes, until brown and crusty.
Cut into wedges and serve with crackers.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Cook wild rice in the boiling water at least 45 minutes. Brown hamburger and onion.
Simmer celery, butter and mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Add water if dries out.

title: peanut butter fluffy frozen pie(1 pie)
directions: Whip cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat sugar and peanut butter slowly; add milk and blend thoroughly into mixture.
Add in topping.
Pour into shell.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
In saucepan on low heat, mix the flour, butter, paprika, chili powder, mustard, cumin seed, catsup and pepper sauce.
When these ingredients are well combined, pour in milk.
Add salt, peppers and cheese (chunked). Serve hot!

title: weight watchers fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken-spaghetti casserole
directions: Combine all soups with 2 cans of water and mix.
Brown onion in the butter and add to the soup.
Add olives, sliced and drained.

title: okra fritters
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by spoonful in hot grease until done.

title: pumpkin sheet cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into sheet cake pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost while still warm.

title: baked ziti casserole
directions: Cook pasta by directions on package. Drain and set aside. In a bowl, combine egg, Ricotta and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce in a 13 x 9 x 2 pan coated with nonstick spray. Top with 1/3 of the pasta and 1/2 Ricotta mixture, 2/3 cup Mozzarella cheese, 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese and 1 cup sauce. Repeat layers. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan. Top with remaining pasta, sauce and cheeses. Cover and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: cold pizza
directions: Spread cream cheese on round platter.
Layer as listed the Heinz chili sauce, then Cheddar cheese, then Mozzarella cheese, then green onion and olives.
Keep refrigerated, but remove 1 hour before serving.

title: low calorie meat loaf
directions: Mix, forming into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Contains 171 calories per serving.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water and sugar; add 7-Up and pineapple juice. Top with scoops of sherbet.

title: rice pancakes
directions: Beat yolks.
Combine with next 4 ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in and cook pancakes on nonstick skillet.

title: vidalia spree
directions: Use a two-quart buttered casserole.
Chop fresh cilantro into 1-inch sprigs.
Layer each of above ingredients, starting with a layer of zucchini on the bottom.
Between layers, sprinkle the seasonings to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add water before placing casserole in oven.
Three layers are a desirable number.

title: cheese pork chops
directions: Melt butter.
Grind up cheese or cheese crackers.
Roll pork chops in butter, then roll in cheese crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Saute onion and bacon until soft.
Add water, vegetables (except tomatoes) and seasonings.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 7 to 10 minutes until vegetables are tender. Add tomatoes and heat.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Put dates, boiling water and baking soda together and let cool.
Mix shortening, sugar, salt, cocoa, eggs and flour and add the cooled date mixture.
Pour into an 8 1/2 x 13-inch baking pan (greased).
Sprinkle chocolate chips, sugar and cut walnuts together on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: brown sugar shews
directions: Stir together egg, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add flour with salt and soda.
Add walnuts.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Spread in well-greased square pan (8-inch).
Bake 18 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cookies will be soft when taken from oven.
Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix or beat together first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Slice apples into pan and cover bottom of pan; top with crumb mixture. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Beat until well mixed.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: soda cracker chocolate candy
directions: Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with foil.
Coat with nonstick cooking spray.
Place crackers in rows on foil.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add the brown sugar and bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and spread until completely covered.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes (crackers will float).
Remove and turn off oven.

title: mexican taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat, drain and rinse.
Add diced onions and taco seasoning.
In a large bowl, mix meat, tomatoes, lettuce, and cheese.
Add the crushed doritos and catalina dressing and toss the salad.
You can add 1 can of light kidney beans, if desired. Serve immediately because lettuce will wilt fast.

title: mom's beef bourbonnaise
directions: Lightly brown beef in butter.
Add garlic and onion.
Saute until transparent.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Stir in soup, wine and water.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add herbs and catsup.
Arrange vegetables on top of meat and gravy.
(Add more water now or while cooking; you want a rich, not-too-thin gravy.) Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 hours, or until meat and vegetables are tender.
(Check frequently to make sure there is sufficient gravy so that mixture does not scorch.)

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spread on 1/2 hamburger bun. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: heavenly peaches
directions: In a large container bowl, take half of angel food cake and tear into chunks for first layer.

title: neptune supreme
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch greased pan with shrimp and flaked crab pieces.
Lightly sprinkle with lemon juice.
In a separate bowl, mix soup, evaporated milk and sour cream.
If too thick, add a little more milk.
Pour over the above.
Sprinkle a light layer of bread crumbs, nuts and shredded Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let rest at least 10 minutes to settle before serving.
Serves 12.

title: rutabaga casserole
directions: Cut rutabaga up and boil until tender.
Once tender, drain and mash until smooth.
Mix in beaten eggs.
Salt and pepper to taste. In separate pan, melt margarine, then stir in bread crumbs.
Set about 1/2 cup bread crumb mixture aside.
Stir remaining bread crumbs into mashed rutabaga mixture.
Top with reserved bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potatoes, brussels sprouts and onions
directions: Scrub potatoes and cook in water in covered pot over high heat until tender, less than 20 minutes.
Slice whole onion.
Heat oil and saute onion until soft.
Spoon into serving dish.
Wash and trim Brussels sprouts.
Add to potatoes and cook 7 to 10 minutes, depending on size.
Remove sprouts with slotted spoon when they are cooked; drain and add to serving dish.
Continue cooking potatoes. Add sugar, soy sauce and pepper to serving dish.
When potatoes are cooked, drain and add to serving dish, cutting into halves or quarters.
Mix well.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix chicken, soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice; pour over broccoli.
Cover with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
You may add cheese, if you prefer.

title: black bean and pepper salad(4 servings)
directions: Drain and rinse the black beans.
Chop the green pepper and the jalapeno pepper.
Grate the green zest from the lime and squeeze 1 tablespoon juice.
Combine the black beans with the green pepper, jalapeno pepper, lime zest and juice, red onion, chopped parsley, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; toss well.

title: texas ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together until well mixed.
Add eggs and stir until well blended; sift dry ingredients together and gradually add creamed mixture.
Stir in coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Drop on foil covered baking sheet by tablespoons, 1 inch apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen large cookies.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Mix flour and seasonings.
Beat egg and water together.
Dip steak in flour, then in egg mixture and again in flour.
Brown both sides in hot oil.
Cover and cook slowly for 20 minutes.

title: children's play dough
directions: Mix ingredients, in order.
Cook in heavy pot over medium heat.
Stir constantly until dough pulls away from sides of the pan.
When cool enough to handle, knead.
Add food coloring. ("Wilton" gives the best results.)
