title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn, oil, meal, sugar, peppers, onion and eggs.
Add grated cheese, milk and a small amount of jalapeno juice.

title: clam and corn chowder
directions: Fry onion in butter until a delicate brown.
Put in saucepan. Add potatoes, corn, milk, clams, salt, pepper and cayenne. Bring to boiling point. Serves 6.

title: dish pan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in dish pan (or very large bowl). Spoon drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: clams casino
directions: Steam clams in a small amount of water.
Mince clams and set aside.
Saute onions, garlic and pimento in olive oil and butter for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Mix minced clams, onions, sauce and crumbled bacon.
Spoon mixture into clam shells.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: peachy parfaits
directions: Mix vanilla pudding and milk.
Stir in cinnamon, Cool Whip and well drained peach slices.
Crumble an oatmeal cookie in the bottom of 6 glasses and top with 1/4 cup pudding mixture.
Repeat layers, then cover and chill.
Garnish with peach slices and oatmeal cookie when ready to serve.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Saute approximately 5 to 10 minutes the sesame seed, almonds and soup mix.
Mix together oil, sugar, vinegar and soy sauce and add to soup mixture.
Add broccoli slaw and toss.
You can add broccoli head, all cut up, if you desire.

title: mom's fudge
directions: Toast pecans in oven.
In large pot, combine sugar and milk. Stir on burner until rolling boil.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Take off burner and stir in remaining ingredients until mixed well; mixture will start to thicken.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or cookie sheet and let set for exactly 6 hours (in or out of fridge) before cutting.
Makes 5 pounds of fudge.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix in blender until thick as you like.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Beat together water, yeast, sugar and beaten eggs and let stand 10 minutes.
Then add sugar, soft margarine and salt.
Then add flour and knead until smooth.
Place in large covered container and refrigerate overnight or up to a week.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half in a 12-inch circle and cut into 16 pie wedges each.
Roll up each wedge, starting at wide end.
Place on greased baking sheet and let rise 2 to 3 hours or until double in size.
Bake at 350°
for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add chili powder, corn, beans and tomato sauce and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour mixture in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover with corn bread batter.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix drained fruit, coconut, marshmallows and sour cream. Refrigerate overnight.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound steak.
Cut into serving size pieces.
In skillet, brown steak in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Stir often.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Prepare potatoes as instructed on package minus margarine and salt.
Once potatoes are prepared and still hot, add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° until light golden brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Place syrup, sugar and water in an iron skillet and cook to the soft ball stage at 230°.
Add peanuts, stir and cook to the crack stage, 301° to 302°.
Turn off the heat.
Stir in until blended the butter, vanilla and baking soda.
Pour onto greased surface, preferably marble.
Turn it at once and stretch it quickly until very thin.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: lasagne
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Peel and mash peaches.
Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Sift flour, spices and salt.
Add soda to buttermilk and add alternately with sifted ingredients to first mixture.
Fold in fresh peaches and juice.
Bake in 9-inch layer pans that are greased and floured. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool layers and ice.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Mix and pour a mixture of 1/2 cup oil and 1/2 cup vinegar mixed over the ingredients.
Stir and store in the refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: Mix dry cake mix, water and eggs.
Drop by tablespoonful on ungreased cookie sheet at least 3-inches apart.
Insert popstick an inch to inch and a half into batter.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool 1 minute and remove from pan.
Cool completely and frost.
Decorate as you wish.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Wash potatoes (do not peel) and cut into quarters (lengthwise).
Add a few at a time in bag and shake to coat potatoes well with cheese mixture.
Melt butter in baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Place potatoes in a layer in pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, turning once or twice during baking.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine macaroni, tuna, soup and cheese.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle chips over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until mixture is hot.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy caramel icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and stir until all boils. Cool 10 minutes. Gradually add powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth.

title: quicou
directions: Cut the Swiss chard tops into very fine strips and wash in several changes of water until it runs almost clear (instead of green). Drain thoroughly and dry with a clean cloth.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Beat eggs and add rest of ingredients. Pour into buttered 8 x 10-inch pan.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Remove 1/2 hour before baking. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
"Great for company brunches."

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and butter.
Add eggs, zucchini, vanilla and walnut flavoring.
Mix well.
Combine flour, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg, soda and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts. Grease and flour 2 bread pans and fill.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pans 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed.
Slice cucumbers and tomatoes. Dice onion.
Mix all ingredients together and let sit overnight.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes. Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake 15 minutes (no longer) at 375°.
Cool 1/2 hour in pan. Empty on towel sprinkled heavily with powdered sugar.
Sprinkle the other side of layer.
Roll towel and cake together loosely. Let sit until completely cool.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat the eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Fold into pumpkin-egg mixture.
Grease a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan; line with waxed paper and grease paper. Pour batter into pan and spread to corners.
Scatter nuts on top. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Run knife around edge of pan and invert on a towel that has been sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Peel off paper and roll while hot, towel and cake together.
Cool. and remove towel.

title: mirial clapp's lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with blender or mixer and pour into pie shell.
Garnish with nuts or chocolate.
Chill in freezer until firm.

title: gooey pecan bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and 1/2 cup margarine.
Press into bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside. Combine 2 eggs, cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 cup margarine. Beat until smooth.
Stir in pecans and pour over cake layer.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil the last 10 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares. Yields 3 dozen.

title: pickled fish
directions: Trim any red or
dark
flesh
off
fish fillets and cut into small pieces.
Place
fish	in
quart
jar	with salt and first cup of vinegar.
Let
stand
in
refrigerator for 6 days shaking jar each day.
After
6 days drain fish and rinse with cold water until water
is
clear.
Cover fish with cold water and let stand for 1
hour.
Mix 1 cup vinegar, sugar, wine and spices and heat until sugar dissolves.
Do not boil.
Let cool before adding to fish.
Pack
fish
in
jar	with
a
layer of onion, then fish, etc.
Add
solution to jar.
Keep in refrigerator for 48 hours then
they	are
ready
to	eat.
Keeps in refrigerator several months.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Peel, seed and slice squash.
Steam in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and mash.
While squash is hot, add butter and let melt.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish and bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until congealed.
During the last few minutes, I add miniature marshmallows to the top and then brown them.

title: seafood stuffing
directions: In a large frying pan, melt margarine.
Add shrimp
meat and toss.
Add scallops next, cutting into bite size pieces if large. Cook only a minute or two.
Add lobster meat.
Pour into a large bowl.
Add crushed Ritz crackers and enough clam juice to moisten. Salt and pepper.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Also, great for stuffing a lobster.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar.
Add pumpkin, baking soda, cinnamon and flour and beat for 2 minutes.
Grease 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet with sides.
Put a sheet of wax paper in pan and press down.
Grease waxed paper.
Pour mixture into pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust; set aside.
Mix flour and cinnamon; slowly add to apple juice.
Pour into 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly until boils and thickens. Remove from heat.
Add apples to hot mixture; stir until well coated.
Spoon into pie crust; dot with some butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 35 minutes. If pie browns to quickly, cover with foil during last 15 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Dump ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan in this order: pineapple spread in bottom; spoon cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over cherry pie filling. Sprinkle top with coconut and nuts.
Do not mix ingredients.
Melt 1 cup margarine and spoon evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: turnip greens
directions: Pick over the leaves of the greens and remove any spotted parts or discolored leaves and stems.
Wash the leaves carefully and thoroughly, until they are free of sand and soil.
The turnip greens will have edible white roots.
Trim the stem top and root part from each and wash thoroughly.
Slice and cut into quarters and cook with the leaves.
Place all in a large saucepan and add a little water, salt to taste and the salt pork.
Bring to a boil; reduce the heat and simmer until just tender, 20 to 30 minutes. Remove from the heat; drain and serve immediately.
Greens are delicious served with pork chops, sweet potatoes and cornbread. Serves 4.

title: brownies
directions: Melt on low heat the butter and unsweetened chocolate.
Add sugar, vanilla extract, eggs and flour.
Also add chopped nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot relish
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook carrots, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain. Return carrots to saucepan.
Add green pepper, pimiento, vinegar, honey and onion.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Combine cream cheese, onion, sour cream, hot sauce and chopped green chilies.
Spread generously over tortillas.
Roll up tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, slice crosswise, making pinwheel pieces.
Will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, salt and peanuts together.
Cook in 10 1/2-inch heavy skillet at medium high heat for 12 minutes, stirring all the time.
When candy is done (be sure not to scorch), add soda and mix well.
Spread out on lightly buttered cookie sheets and cool.

title: layered squash
directions: Grease or butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Layer in the order given. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil.
Do not use mixer. Add other ingredients and mix.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and follow instructions on package of taco mix to make meat mixture.
Meanwhile, place lettuce, tomatoes and crumbled chips in 1 large bowl or individual salad bowls.
Top with French dressing, sauce and hot meat mixture.
Can garnish with sour cream.

title: toss salad dressing
directions: Mix well; shake all ingredients together.
Makes one quart.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar. Set aside.

title: a special love recipe
directions: Prepare with one 15 minute massage kneading, wrapping and stirring.

title: speedy shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter; add onions, garlic, lemon rind, lemon juice and salt. Cook 2 to 3 minutes, until bubbly. Reduce heat; add shrimp and cook 5 minutes, until shrimp is pink. Stir constantly. Add parsley and hot sauce and toss with cooked pasta.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Cream together.
Spread over baked pie.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Chill overnight or put in freezer for later date.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour, salt, sugar and onion.
Stir in cream and heat through but do not boil.
In other pan, cook beans until tender, then drain.
Combine sour cream mixture with beans. Add Swiss cheese and turn into casserole.
Top with corn flakes. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt butter and drain sweet potatoes.
Mix all ingredients, except coconut.
Blend well.
Place in 1-quart casserole and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Add coconut to top of casserole, return to oven to brown.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water, melt chocolate and margarine.
Add condensed milk, vanilla and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Makes 1 1/3 cups sauce.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over pretzels.
Stir to coat. Pour into a 15 x 10 baking pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs with salt.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add flour with baking powder.
Add milk with Crisco; add vanilla or lemon.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: frijoles mexicanos(mexican beans)
directions: Wash beans, removing any loose skins or shriveled beans.
Put beans in a large pot.
Add water, cumin and garlic.
Cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Add bacon fat, salt and onion and continue cooking until beans are tender, approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Rinse cabbage; boil whole in salted water for 5 minutes. Drain well; mix together remaining ingredients except oil and water.
Spread leaves gently; insert some stuffing and wrap until all is used.
Place in baking dish and cover with oil, add water to 1/2 inch.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until cabbage is tender.
Add hot water to pan if dry.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Melt fat in skillet and brown hamburger in it. Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce. Cover and cook slowly 15 to 20 minutes. Cook noodles and drain well. Chop scallions or onions and mix with the softened cream cheese and sour cream. Put layer of 1/3 of noodles in bottom of large casserole dish. Spread 1/3 of onion mixture over first layer. Cover these with 1/3 of meat sauce. Repeat twice more. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: squash pie
directions: Whip sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add squash, margarine, vanilla, nutmeg, salt and milk.
Mix flour and 1 teaspoon sugar and sprinkle over crust before filling.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs together first. Add rest of ingredients. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put brown sugar and cinnamon in a brown lunch bag.
Cut each biscuit into
sections and drop into lunch bag.	Shake until the
biscuit
sections
are coated.
Drop into a greased Bundt pan.
Continue
until
all	biscuits are done.
Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture on top and add the other 3/4 cup brown sugar.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven
to
Mix
the
flour and sugar in a bowl; add
the
peaches
and syrup; stir.
Melt the margarine; pour into a
baking
dish.
Pour the cobbler mixture into the middle of the baking dish so the margarine surrounds the sides of the
dish. Bake
at
for
40 to 45 minutes, checking often for desired browning.

title: mother's rice pudding
directions: In a large saucepan, stir flour into sugar.
Beat in eggs, milk and raisins and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Stir in vanilla and rice.
Pour into greased baking dish; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Bring sugar and margarine to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Beat until cool and ready to spread.

title: white chili
directions: Simmer beans 2 minutes.
Cook chicken and drain.
Put all ingredients in crock pot and simmer until tender.

title: german cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add yolks of eggs and beat well. Add dry and then liquid ingredients, small amounts at a time.
Then add nuts and raisins and last fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Sprinkle 10x sugar on top after baking.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown in skillet the ground beef, onion and chili powder.
Add the next 6 ingredients in a large pan and bring to a boil on low heat, stirring often.
When it has come to a boil, add the ground beef and mix well. In a large dish, put a layer of tortillas and pour some of mixture on them.
Continue these layers until all of both are used.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Generously grease 9-inch square pan with oil.
Heat in oven while mixing batter.
Beat eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Add cornmeal; beat well.
Add salt.
Pour into hot pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish; mix flour, milk and sugar. Pour into baking dish. Add fruit; bake until crust is brown at 350°.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain beans and add equal amount of water.
In a heavy saucepan, simmer beans with meat and onion for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; add egg, vanilla and milk. Beat until smooth.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 9 minutes. Remove from oven and place a large marshmallow on top of each cookie.
Return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and press marshmallow down to cover cookie.
Cool.
Frost with Chocolate Frosting.

title: champagne salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together with mixer until fluffy. Fold in remaining ingredients gently. Mix well and freeze until serving time.

title: egg salad spread
directions: Chop eggs with blending fork or grate on medium grater until pulverized.
Add enough mayonnaise to make of spreading consistency.
Season with spices and bacon to taste.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oven barbecued steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with the mixture. Brown slowly on both sides in hot fat.
Spoon off excess fat.

title: rosemary's chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat together butter and sugar with electric mixer until light and creamy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in the vanilla and eggs until smooth.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into cubes.
Mix flour and paprika until flour mixture is well coated.
Heat oil in pan.
Add chopped onion and meat; stir until meat is brown.
If it doesn't look red enough, add more paprika to this mixture.
Add beef consomme and 1 can water; let simmer until meat is tender over low heat.
Cook noodles according to directions.
When noodles are drained, add sour cream to meat mixture and stir well.
Pour meat mixture over noodles and serve.

title: black forest torte
directions: Cut pound cake into 1/2-inch cubes.
Arrange in 2-quart dessert bowl.
Prepare pudding mix according to package.
Pour over pound cake.
Spoon pie filling over pudding and spread whipped topping over pie filling.
Chill.
Sprinkle over toasted almonds.
Serves 10.

title: snickers cake
directions: Melt caramels, milk and oleo.
(I use microwave.)
Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour half of cake batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to instructions.
Set in refrigerator.
Separate eggs; put yolks in separate medium bowl. Stir; add milk.
Stir in lemon juice little at a time.
Fold in Dream Whip.
(Fold in Nilla wafer prepared crust.)
Whip egg whites; add 5 to 6 tablespoons sugar.
Spread on pie.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: braised pork chops and apples
directions: Brown pork chops in oil on both sides until golden brown in a large skillet.
Pour off fat.
Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Add broth and thyme; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 50 minutes, spooning pan liquid over chops occasionally.
Add apples.
Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes longer or until done.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: savory fried rice
directions: Saute onions in butter for 5 minutes.
Add rice and herbs. Cook until rice begins to brown.
Add chicken bouillon, cover saucepan and simmer until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Salt to taste.
Serves 6.

title: french seafood coquilles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly all ingredients, except cheese.
Place 1 cup mixture in each of 5 or 6 baking shells or individual casseroles.
Place shells on baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes; remove from oven.
Top shells with cheese and bake 2 or 3 minutes longer.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix in blender or large jar and shake vigorously.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chops 'n sour cream
directions: Brown chops, arrange in baking dish and salt.
Sprinkle onions on top, potatoes and salt.
Pour sour cream over all.
Cover. Bake 1 hour in moderate oven until tender.

title: mom's easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain, then add tomato sauce, water and salt. Heat to a boil.
Squeeze excess liquid from spinach.
In blender or food processor, add spinach, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Blend until smooth.
In 3-quart baking dish, layer sauce and uncooked lasagna.
Spread with spinach filling.
Continue layers of sauce, cheese, lasagna and sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut squares
directions: Pour over mixture 1 1/2 cups hot milk.
Bake at 350°.

title: orange mint punch
directions: Combine sugar with water and boil 10 minutes.
Place lemon juice, orange juice, orange rind and mint leaves in large pitcher. Pour sugar and water mixture over ingredients in pitcher.
Cover and let set for 1 hour.
Strain and add ginger ale to taste.

title: cleo's tea cakes
directions: Beat lard and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and salt.
Add alternately flour and beaten eggs.
Dough should be firm but not sticky.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick and cook on greased cookie sheets at 375° until brown on edges or make into rolls and refrigerate overnight.
Slice 1/4 inch thick and bake as usual.
Let cool in pan for 3 minutes before removing.

title: grandma's shortbread
directions: Mix 3 ingredients.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut into shapes (no larger than 1-inch circle, star etc.).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick each cookie 3 times with fork.
Bake 35 - 40 minutes at 300° or until set.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: In blender or food processor, combine cream cheese, cottage cheese, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Blend until smooth.
Scoop mixture into serving bowl and stir in remaining ingredients. Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve as dip for vegetables or spread on bread.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: zucchini pickle relish(use very mature zucchini)
directions: Mix zucchini, onion and peppers with salt and let set overnight.
In the morning, drain and rinse good with cold tap water.
Drain well.

title: microwave peanut butter and jam bars
directions: Combine butter, peanut butter, sugars and egg; beat well. Add flour and beat on low speed until mixture is crumbly. Reserve 1 cup crumbs. Press remaining crumbs into 8-inch square glass baking dish. Place on an inverted plate to elevate dish in oven. Cook at Medium 6 1/2 minutes or until base looks dry, rotating dish if necessary. Spread jam on base to within 1/2-inch of edge. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Cook at Medium 6 to 7 minutes or until jam bubbles near the center, rotating dish once. Cool.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in saucepan until warm.
Add yeast. When yeast is bubbly, stir in eggs.
Add flour gradually while kneading.
Place in a large greased bowl and let rise in a warm place for 2 hours until double in size.
Punch down lightly and divide into thirds.
Roll 1/3 of the dough into a 12-inch circle. Cut into 8 pieces, like a pie, then roll each piece from the wide end to the pointed end.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place rolls on greased baking sheet and let rise again, 30 minutes or until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, but watch carefully so they don't burn.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: tuna stuff
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan, add unheated soups and rinse cans with milk; add milk, tuna and half the potato chips.
Mix well.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top to cover.
Bake at 325° until warm.
Serve with salad or favorite vegetable.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Pour into ungreased 9x13 pan and bake at 350° till done.

title: chocolate crunch
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cover cookie sheet (11 x 17-inch) with foil, then cover foil with saltine crackers, making sure pan is completely covered (see note).
Heat the butter and sugar until smooth.
Cover saltines with mixture.
Spoon over and cover well. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Check after 15 minutes so it doesn't burn.
Remove from oven.
Cover with the chocolate bits.
When melted, spread over saltines.
Put in freezer or refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours, until hard.
Break into bite size pieces.

title: six-layer dinner
directions: Place layers in greased 2-quart casserole.
Season layers with salt and pepper. Garnish with green pepper slices.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size portions, roll in flour and brown in butter in skillet. In large, deep baking dish, add tomatoes, onion, green pepper and bayleaf. Cook at 350° for 90 minutes. Add peas, carrots and steak, salt and pepper to taste. Add water or V-8, as needed. Bake an additional 45 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix vegetables (diced) together with plain salt.
Let stand for 10 minutes .
Drain well.
Add vinegar, sugar and spices. Cook for 20 minutes.
Fill in clean jars.
For a good seal, I put in pressure cooker for 5 minutes on 5 pounds pressure.

title: egg and ham strata
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Cut off crust of bread and line bottom of pan with bread.
Brown sausage and drain. Put on top of bread.
Add grated Cheddar cheese and mushrooms. Mix together the eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over top of mushrooms.
Chill overnight.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour on top. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla; stir in flour, 1 cup at a time. Fold in coconut.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and then at 350° for 30 more minutes.

title: diet orange fluff
directions: Sprinkle orange jello over cottage cheese and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together, then add cottage cheese and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix, eggs, corn and sour cream together.
Add sausage, onion, cheese and pepper.
Bake in large skillet at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix crackers and butter; put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar, then mix with Dream Whip and spread over cracker crumb crust.
Next, spread pie filling over cream cheese.
Chill overnight.
Colorful and tasty.

title: marilyn's pepper steak and rice
directions: Cut round steak into 1/4-inch strips and sprinkle paprika onto the strips. Slice onion and separate into rings. Also, slice bell peppers into thin strips. In a very large skillet, brown meat in butter on medium-high heat. Add beef broth. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until meat is tender. During this time, prepare the rice. Add onion and bell pepper to the meat and cook for 5 minutes. In a small bowl, mix cornstarch, water and soy sauce until smooth. Add to meat mixture and continue to simmer until vegetables are tender and sauce is thick. Spread cooked rice in a 9 x 13 dish and pour meat mixture over rice. Enjoy.

title: daniel and rebecca's sauerkraut with beer
directions: Rinse sauerkraut in cold water.
Drain and squeeze thoroughly. Place in crock-pot or casserole with tight fitting lid with rest of ingredients.
If using crock-pot set on high for 1/2 hour to heat everything, then on low for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
If using casserole or Dutch oven, 3 hours at 300°.

title: buffet supper
directions: In large skillet saute onion and broccoli in butter until tender.
Stir in Cheez Whiz, soup and milk until smooth.
Add chopped chicken.
Put rice into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over rice.
Bake uncovered for 25 to 30 minutes at 325° or until heated through.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: cheese log
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix together the ingredients.
Shape in log or ball.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Chill.
I sometimes roll the ball or log in chopped pecans.
Will freeze.

title: lemon salad
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
Cool.
In large bowl, combine pudding with remaining ingredients; stir gently. Cover; refrigerate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzels when cooled.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries until thick.
Pour over Cool Whip layer.
Let set in fridge 1 hour before serving.

title: arkansas pecan cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and whole egg until fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well after each addition. Stir flour, baking powder and salt together. Add to creamed mixture alternately with water. Stir until smooth. Grease a 10-inch tube pan and line bottom only with waxed paper. Pour half the batter into pan. Drop Pecan Mixture by spoonfuls on batter, then top with remaining batter. Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool cake in pan on rack; turn out.

title: date roll cookies
directions: Cook dates, water and sugar until thick and add nuts.
Mix oleo, brown sugar and egg; add flour, soda and salt.
Divide dough into 2 parts and roll to 1/2-inch or 1/4-inch and spread with date mixture.
Roll like a jelly roll, wrap in Handi-Wrap or wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and cook on greased cookie sheet at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: onion shortcake
directions: Saute onion in margarine; add sour cream and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Set
aside.
Combine cornbread mix, creamed corn and egg. Pat corn mixture
into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour onion mixture on top of cornbread, then top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350°
until
golden brown, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: quick chili burgers
directions: In skillet, brown beef; stir to separate meat.
Blend in soup and water.
Heat; stir now and then.
Serve in buns; top with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In large frying pan saute in hot oil for 5 minutes the squash and onions.
Drain well.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots. Fold in the squash and onion mixture.
Combine in separate bowl the stuffing and melted butter.
In 9 x 9 x 2-inch casserole spread 1/2 of stuffing.
Add all of squash mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in 1/2.
Place cut side down.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Mix other ingredients.
Fill squash.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and chopped onion until done; drain.
Add green chilies, enchilada sauce, chicken soup, mushroom soup and approximately 2 cups crunched tortilla chips.
Put into lightly greased pan; top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: haddock baked with cheese
directions: Thaw fillets just enough to separate, sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place in greased shallow baking pan.
Saute minced onion in butter until delicately browned. Add salt, pepper and cheese; toss together lightly to mix.
Spread mixture over fillets, pressing down firmly.
Pour 1/2-cup milk around fish and bake in hot oven (400°) for 35 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: baked ham
directions: Cut excess fat off hen.
Score top and sides with mustard. Cover that with a layer of brown sugar.
Bake in oven at 275°, basting every 20 minutes with
Coca-Cola, pineapple juice and drippings.
Bake, uncovered, until very hot through ham, about 20 or 25 minutes per pound.

title: dot's salad
directions: Separate and cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Combine with onion, cheese and bacon in large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight; mix before serving.

title: coconut almond carrot ring
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat sugar and oil at medium speed until well mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in carrots, nuts, raisins and 2/3 cup coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done in center.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly. Frost with cream cheese frosting and cover with remaining coconut.

title: garlic roasted chicken
directions: In a large roasting pan, place chicken, potatoes and garlic. Pour butter over all and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes, basting frequently with the pan juices.
Heat honey; baste over chicken.
Spoon pan juices over potatoes and garlic. Bake 20 minutes longer or until chicken is tender.

title: tuna-noodle salad casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Combine noodles, drained tuna, sweet peas, mayonnaise, soup, milk, onion, pimento and seasonings.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake about 20 minutes at 400°.

title: zippy franks
directions: Melt jelly with mustard and horseradish; cut up hot dogs into small pieces or use cocktail franks.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: busy day barbecue
directions: Cook onion slices in hot fat until tender.
Mix and add other ingredients, except Spam.
Add strips of luncheon meat.
Heat to boiling.
Spoon meat sauce over hot, fluffy rice.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: blooming onion
directions: Lightly grease a large baking pan.
Peel the onions, cut the bottom level but leave the core intact.

title: northern-style lasagna
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Spoon off fat.
Add beef and onion.
Cook until meat is brown.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and set aside.
In small bowl, combine soup and milk.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together Cheddar cheese, 1 package Mozzarella cheese and Ricotta cheese.
Brown ground beef; drain, then add Ragu sauce.
Cook shells as directed, then rinse in cold water.

title: viennese souffle(kaiserschmarrn)
directions: Mix egg yolks with flour, then add sugar, then vanilla, then cream.
Add beaten egg whites last.
Melt the butter in a large pan.
Pour the whole mixture in and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Let it stand a short time before serving.
Tear with fork and return to oven briefly.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Mix bacalaitos according to instructions on box.
Mix well and pour mixture in a deep bowl.
Add adobo if desired.
Heat pan with oil till hot.
Cut eggplant into slices.
Dip into the bacalaito mixture and place in pan.
Cook each side for 1-2 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool for a few minutes before serving.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs. Sift dry ingredients together and gradually add to egg mixture. Cover dough and chill. Roll to desired thickness on floured board with powdered sugar only.
Also dip cookie cutters in powdered sugar to cut out cookies.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: shipwreck
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place half of slices in a greased casserole.
Brown ground beef.
Add to casserole.
Mix salt, pepper, beans and onions.
Add to casserole.
Arrange remaining potatoes on top.
Combine tomato soup and water.
Spoon evenly over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Fix Rice-A-Roni as directed on box.
After rice is done, add cream soup.
Layer in casserole dish Rice-A-Roni mixture, shredded chicken, cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted and bubbling.
You can increase or decrease chicken.

title: macaroni salad 2
directions: Cook macaroni in water until done.
Rinse in cold water. Drain. Add celery, bell pepper, tomatoes and pimento.
Add mayonnaise and salt. Stir to mix. Chill.

title: zucchini and cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put into a medium sized well buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple bubble cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients and pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Stir all ingredients thoroughly in large bowl.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or just until set (do not overbake).
Let stand 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Store covered. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: marra's salsa
directions: Dice onions, peppers and tomatoes and place in a pan to heat. Add garlic powder, chili powder, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Cook slowly until the vegetables are soft.
Add the tomato paste, bring to a boil again.
Remove from heat and cool.
Eat with chips of your choice.

title: hamburger and tater tots
directions: Lightly brown and salt ground beef and diced onion.
Add mushroom soup, diluted with water.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Place Tater Tots on top of ground beef mixture.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Yields 8 servings.

title: caramel candy
directions: Boil together sugar, molasses and salt to 245°.
Add butter and cream; boil to 242°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Be careful to stir often while cooking, especially near the end.
Pour into a well buttered 5 x 10-inch pan.
Cool until cold.
Cut in small squares and wrap in wax paper.

title: 12 layer salad
directions: Mix each package of jello, separately, with 1 cup boiling water. Divide in half. Pour first half in pan. Chill in freezer for 10 to 15 minutes. Mix second half with 1/3 cup sour cream or Cool Whip. Pour over first layer; chill. Continue layers alternately until all 12 layers are done.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch cake pan with butter.
Add the can of crushed pineapple on bottom.
Spread cherry pie filling with juice over pineapple.
Sprinkle white cake mix over top.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over cake mix.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popped popcorn in a large roaster pan.
Bring brown sugar, Karo syrup and margarine to a boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add soda, salt and vanilla.
Pour over popped popcorn. Bake at 250° for 40 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on waxed paper.
Can freeze.
Can add peanuts while baking.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream butter.
Add mashed bananas.
Blend in egg; beat well. Add combined dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly with electric mixer on low speed.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: four layered dessert(very low sugar)
directions: Mix and press into bottom of an 8 x 11-inch glass cake dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Set aside to cool.

title: cream beef on toast
directions: Braise meat, then add onions and butter.
After
2 minutes, add flour and make a gravy.
Add salt, pepper and garlic.
Stir often.
Cook on low heat.
Serve on toast.

title: seven layer cookie bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter. Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients in order listed.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: carrot-nut loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly, adding bread crumbs as needed.
Bake in oiled pan 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with tomato sauce or white sauce. Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring milk, sugar and margarine to boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and Marshmallow Creme. Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: salmon loaf(microwave)
directions: In medium bowl combine all ingredients, except butter. Garnish.
Add 2 teaspoons butter and mix well.
Grease 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with remaining butter.
Spoon in salmon mixture and smooth top.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
(Center should be firm.)
Let stand 5 minutes.
Invert onto platter and garnish. Serves 4.

title: cookie icing recipe
directions: Place sugar and milk in bowl; stir until mixed thoroughly. Add corn syrup and mix well.
For a thinner icing, add small amounts of corn syrup until desired consistency is reached.
This icing dries to a shiny, hard finish.

title: chocolate cake to the max
directions: Allow butter and eggs to stand at room temperature for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, lightly grease bottoms of 3 (8 x 1 1/2-inch) round cake pans. Line bottoms of pans with waxed paper. Grease and lightly flour bottoms and sides of pans (or grease one 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan); set pans aside.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add flour, sugar, salt and pepper to well-beaten eggs.
Add milk, corn and melted butter.
Pour into hot buttered baking dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until firm and lightly brown.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and flour; mix well.
In small bowl, mix 1 cup milk with slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add this to the flour mixture, along with remaining cup of milk.
Cook until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Top with meringue.

title: carmel oatmeal chews
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add margarine, mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of prepared pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Top with nuts and chocolate bits.
In medium saucepan, melt caramels with water over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Drizzle over chocolate and nuts to within 1/4-inch of pan edges.
Sprinkle with reserved oatmeal mixture.
Continue baking 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Chill until chocolate is set.
Cut into bars and store tightly covered in a cool dry place.

title: lemon chicken i
directions: Place chicken in baking pan.
Insert 1 whole lemon in cavity of chicken.
Squeeze 1/2 lemon over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours, depending on size.

title: fudgemallow raisin candy
directions: Microwave chocolate and peanut butter in 2-quart bowl on medium 2 to 3 minutes or until melted, stirring after each minute. Fold in marshmallows and raisins.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm; cut into squares.
Makes approximately 24.

title: victor's chocolate chip cookie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix with graham crackers and press firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chips evenly over crumbs. Spread nuts.
Pour condensed milk all over.
Do not pat down. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Should be slightly browned on top; watch closely.
Cool 8 hours.
Sift powdered sugar on top and cut into squares.

title: spaghetti meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased casserole dish. Press down with spoon and bake 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, mix together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon. Stir together.
In larger bowl, blend together the sugar and oil until fluffy.
Gradually add the eggs, pumpkin and water.
Mix well.
Add the flour mixture, a little at a time.
Stir well.
Pour batter into greased loaf pans and add raisins or chopped nuts to the batter before baking to give the bread added flavor.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package. Add sweetened condensed milk and thawed Cool Whip. Layer vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mix. This makes a large amount.

title: grand grasshopper pie
directions: In a bowl, combine the crushed chocolate wafers and the butter.
Turn into 9-inch plate and press evenly into the bottom and sides.
Chill for about an hour or until firm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt the
oleo	and
add
about
tablespoon flour or cornstarch to
make
a
paste.
Add milk and heat.	Add cheese and stir
until
melted.
Add
salt and pepper to taste.
Peel potatoes and slice.
Layer potatoes, onion and ham.
Pour milk mixture over this.	You
may have to add a little more milk to cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Use a deep pan to keep it from boiling over.

title: egg-cheese bake(receives raves for brunch)
directions: Pour milk over bread cubes to soak.
Use the cut off crusts by popping them into the oven at 350° until dry and golden.
Remove from oven and crush to use as garnish during assembly of dish. Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in skillet.
Add eggs and begin to scramble.
Drain milk from soaking bread cubes and lightly scramble milk into eggs. then add bread cubes to egg mixture, mix well. While still soft, add skillet contents to greased casserole.
Place cheese on top.
Cover with crushed bread crumbs, melted margarine and bacon bits.
Bake at 375° until cheese bubbles (approximately 10 minutes).

title: southwest layered taco dip
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Combine with the raw turkey, onion and chili powder in a shallow 2-quart microwave dish, preferably transparent.
Cover and microwave on High 8 to 9 minutes, stirring to mash beans and break up meat every 3 minutes until turkey is white.
Stir in salsa.
Sprinkle with cheese and microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate chip cookies(makes 14 to 15 dozen)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Then add dry ingredients, and 1 large bag chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonsful on cookie sheet and bake at 350° 14 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Chip butter in pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add vanilla and Cool Whip; mix.
Pour into pie shells.
Top with blueberry pie filling. Refrigerate.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Combine rhubarb and 1/2 cup sugar in mixing bowl.
Let stand until batter is mixed.
Cream together shortening and 1 1/2 cup sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and rhubarb last.
Pour into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend and serve as a dip for strawberries or chunks of assorted fruits such as pineapple, grapes, apples and bananas.

title: billy's onion pretzels
directions: Melt butter; mix in dry onion soup mix.
Break up pretzels. Add mixture over pretzels so pretzels are covered.
Cook at 200° for 1 hour, turning often.
Enjoy.
Great for a party.

title: greg's artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine artichokes and lemon juice.
Add dash of Tabasco, oregano, basil, garlic, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Mix in mayo.
Mix in Parmesan cheese. Add olives, red pepper and mushrooms.
Empty into 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish or casserole.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until top turns brown.
Serve immediately with thinly sliced French or Italian bread.
This can be prepared in advance and baked when needed. Keep refrigerated.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin in a large bowl.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add into pumpkin mixture. Pour into ungreased oblong baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soften relish and cheese.
Mix well and freeze.
Can be refrozen.
Serves 6 to 9.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cook 5 minutes, then add 3 large marshmallows. Stir to cool. Frost layers and top.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Layer ingredients in order starting with pie filling and ending with chopped pecans.
Don't stir!
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: teen-agers cocktail
directions: Combine orange juice, lemon juice and egg whites in mixer jar. Mix well for about 1 minute.
Add sherbet and mix about 1 1/2 minutes.

title: hot or cold shrimp pasta salad
directions: In a large saucepan or wok, lightly saute the garlic in olive oil.
Do not brown.
Add shrimp and cook 1 minute.
Add sour cream, peas, basil, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Heat through.
Add corkscrew pasta.
Enjoy!
Great hot or cold.

title: party sandwich spread
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Use your favorite chips to serve.

title: garlic bread
directions: Cream butter and add minced garlic; mix very well.
Spread over bread and bake until golden brown.

title: can apple crumb cake
directions: Mix cake according to box.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Spread 1/2 can apples on top, then 1/2 crumb mix.; then cake, apples, and crumb mix.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Melt shortening, combine with brown sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Set aside to cool.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Add eggs to cooled sugar mixture; beat well. Stir in reserved dry ingredients, nuts and chips.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: joan's creative stove top
directions: Prepare dressing per package directions; mix in sauteed celery, onion and mushrooms.
Before serving (while still hot), stir in orange marmalade.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In food processor, combine cucumbers, onions and bell pepper. Mix celery seed, salt, sugar and vinegar.
Heat.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: raw apple spice cake with browned butter icing
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and orange peel, mixing well.
Sift flour with spices and soda and add to creamed mixture. Add apples, nuts and raisins.
Spread into greased and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: Put hot dogs in large pan.
Add ketchup, brown sugar and bourbon.
Add to hot dogs and simmer.
The longer they simmer the better they are.
Pour into chafing dish.
Serve warm.

title: vidalia divan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 2-quart casserole with Pam.
In large bowl, combine chicken, Vidalias, sour cream, soup and cheese.
In small bowl, combine bread crumbs, margarine and poppy seed; mix well.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until crumbs are golden brown and filling is bubbly.

title: shrimp dip
directions: *Cream cheese should be at room temperature.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; arrange in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch dish. Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
Add cooked chicken and cheese; top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shake(weight watchers 2 points)
directions: Put all in blender and process until smooth and thick.

title: drop cookies
directions: Blend sugars and shortening; add beaten eggs, then sour cream or buttermilk that has been mixed
with soda. Add sifted flour, nutmeg, ginger, baking powder, salt and vanilla. Add chocolate bits or raisins and nuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: funke chicken
directions: Boil or microwave chicken until cooked; drain.
Cube and set aside.
In bowl, mix sour cream, milk and soup.
Prepare stuffing mix according to directions on package.

title: jell-o salad
directions: Mix together well and chill.
Use low fat cottage cheese, fat-free Cool Whip, and sugar-free Jell-O for a healthier choice.

title: mama's cornbread
directions: Sift cornmeal, add buttermilk, a pinch of soda and a pinch of salt.
Add enough water to make thick enough to be shaped into pones.
Cover top of each pone with bacon grease.
Bake at 450° until brown.
(These are easy to make, as I learned to make them when I was 10 years old.)

title: reunion rolls
directions: Scald milk. Stir in sugar, salt and butter. Cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast in warm water. Stir until dissolved. Add lukewarm milk mixture. Add beaten eggs and flour. Beat until smooth. Add and stir in remaining flour. Knead about 10 minutes. Place in a warm place until doubled in bulk (about 1 hour). Punch down and divide in half, then each half into 12 equal parts and shape into balls. Place about 2-inches apart on a greased baking sheet. Cover. Let rise until double in bulk. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Place 6 slices of bread in 3-quart baking dish.
Spread 1/2 of cheese and sausage (mixed) over that.
Combine well beaten eggs and milk and pour over above.
Lay remaining 6 slices of bread on top and balance of sausage and cheese on top of bread.
Press down until milk comes through.
Refrigerate overnight, uncovered.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add other ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole; top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until crumbs are browned.

title: lemon lush
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream butter and flour to make crust. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Set aside to cool.

title: saucepan cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oleo, salt and dates; cook in heavy saucepan until it hangs together, stirring constantly, 7 to 10 minutes. Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Form balls in teaspoon size.
Roll balls in coconut and lay on tray to cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all but cheese and potato chips. Put in casserole.
Cover with cheese and chips.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple-banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Thoroughly mix moist ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients and thoroughly mix together. Butter bottom only of 2 (9-inch) loaf pans.
Pour mixture evenly into two pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean from the center.

title: chicken and mixed vegetable stew
directions: Heat vegetable oil in heavy, large Dutch oven over medium heat. Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
Add chicken to pot in batches and cook until light brown, about 5 minutes per side. Transfer chicken to bowl.
Pour off fat from pot and discard.
Add butter to same pot and melt over medium heat.
Add sliced parsnips, carrots, leeks and potatoes and stir to coat.
Cook 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add flour and stir 2 minutes.
Gradually mix in chicken broth.
Increase heat and bring to boil.

Return chicken to same pot; add 1 tablespoon tarragon and bay leaf. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until chicken and vegetables are cooked through, turning chicken occasionally, for about 30 minutes. Using tongs; transfer chicken pieces to large shallow bowl and tent with foil.
Add whipping cream to pot; increase heat.
Simmer until liquid thickens to sauce consistency, about 10 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Mix in remaining tablespoon tarragon.
Season stew to taste with salt and pepper.
Spoon sauce and vegetables over chicken and serve.

title: rita's squash souffle
directions: Use a large deep, fluted
dish and drip pan under dish. Cook cut up squash
and
onion.
Crumble
the crackers.
Shred the cheese.
Combine all in
fluted baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour, uncovered.
Should
be firm in center when cooked completely.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Heat to boiling first 4 ingredients.
Add cornstarch to thicken.
Pour into pie shell.
Add top pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mandarin spinach delight
directions: Wash and drain spinach.
Place in a large bowl.
Add other ingredients, except dressing; toss with salad servers.
Chill until you serve with the cup of salad dressing.

title: con carne-delphia dip
directions: Heat can of chili con carne to almost a boil.
Melt Philadelphia cream cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into bowl and serve as a dip.

title: grilled potato wedges
directions: Boil potatoes for about 20 minutes, until just tender.
Allow to cool, then cut lengthwise into quarters.
In small bowl, combine olive oil and garlic; brush potato wedges with garlic flavored oil.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Grill or boil 5 to 6 minutes, until hot and lightly browned.

title: robin russe(pet)
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch cake pan, put diced apple (including skin and seeds), raisins, noodles and sand; set aside.
Put suet through meat grinder, then melt down in double boiler.
Allow suet to cool and harden slightly.
Reheat and pour over ingredients in pan. Refrigerate to harden; cut into pieces and serve on tray or ground feeder.

title: garlic shrimp
directions: In saucepan, heat oil, oregano and butter.
Then add shrimp, garlic and wine.
Cook until shrimp is done, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix celery and grated onion. Cover with Wish-Bone dressing. Place in a covered container in the refrigerator for at least 12 hours. Grate shrimp. Drain excess dressing from celery and onion mixture. Add to grated shrimp. Use enough mayonnaise to form a consistency for dip. Add cream cheese after beating smooth. Add salt, pepper and a dash of garlic powder. Mix well. Yields about 3 cups. Serve with chips or toasted bread squares. Serves 12.

title: potato and chicken casserole
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with grated carrots.
(Have chicken cooked and diced.) Place over carrots.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix both cans of soup with about 1/2 can water.
Pour over mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes until potatoes are done.

title: cheese squares
directions: Melt margarine in a cooking pan.
Combine eggs, milk, flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat well.
Add spinach and cheese to egg mixture; mix well.
Pour into pan and mix with margarine.
Spread evenly.
Bake 35 minutes or until set.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: cheesy potato fans
directions: Wash and dry potatoes.
Cut almost through potato crosswise, forming 1/4-inch slices that are still held together on one side. Let stand in ice water about 5 minutes to help open slices.
Place butter in small glass dish.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 45 to 60 seconds, or until melted.
Drain potatoes.
Place in a 12 x 8-inch microwave-safe baking dish, making potatoes fan open. Brush potatoes with about 1/2 the butter, coating between the slices.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 10 minutes, rearranging potatoes once.

title: avocado delight
directions: Peel avocado and cut in half.
Fill cavity with cranberry sauce and top with whipped cream.

title: anne's eggplant casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion until transparent, in oil.
Add eggplant and stir well.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add seasonings, raisins, sugar and the can of tomatoes with juice.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, then pour into a casserole dish and put into a 325° oven for about 1 hour to thicken and bring it all together. Meanwhile, put the rice on to cook.
Serve over the hot rice.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Heat to boil.
Thicken with cornstarch and water.

title: bevs' chili
directions: Cook hamburg, sausage pepperoni, onion and green pepper in a skillet.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt butter and add sugar and eggs, then stir in all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bacon cheese snacks
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Spread on rye rounds and sprinkle with bacon bits.
Heat in 375° oven until cheese melts. Serve hot.
Makes snacks for 8.

title: chocolate oat bars
directions: Cream together the butter and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together and add the flour, soda and salt.
Add oats.
Over low heat, melt together the chips, milk, butter and salt.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Pat 2/3 of dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chocolate mixture over dough, then dot with remaining 1/3 dough.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh cherry pie
directions: Prepare pastry for 8-inch lattice top pie; line 8-inch pie plate with pastry.
Combine cherries, sugar, flour and dash of salt.
Turn into pastry lined pie plate; dot with butter.
Adjust lattice top; seal.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cheese-rice crispy(appetizer-snack)
directions: Mix cheese and margarine; add flour and mix well.
Add cereal; mix well.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten each ball with a fork and bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cut up peaches and put into bottom of casserole dish. Place bread evenly on top of peaches. Mix other ingredients and pour evenly over bread. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop mixture from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 30 to 34 cookies.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello with water, add pineapple and pie filling.
Add pecans.
Refrigerate to congeal.
Top with mixture of cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.

title: percolator punch
directions: Put juice and water in percolator.
Put remaining ingredients in basket and percolate.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Peel rinds and remove watermelon pulp.
Cut rind into 4-inch long pieces.
Pour sugar over rinds and let set overnight.
Cook rinds and sugar until it forms a light syrup (approximately 2 to 3 hours), then place in hot scalded jars and seal.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, for five minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
This will foam up in pan.
Gradually pour over popped corn and nuts, mixing well.

title: honey-glazed baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 2 tablespoon butter in a shallow baking dish just large enough to hold chicken in a single layer. Mix flour, garlic salt and pepper together.
Then coat chicken pieces.
Arrange chicken, skin side down, in butter.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: chile
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion and pepper and saute.
Add beans and tomatoes.
Add spices.
Simmer 3 hours.

title: maple nut party mix(snacks)
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Melt oleo; mix in brown sugar and maple flavoring.
Mix cereal and nuts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle with oleo mix.
Stir until well coated.
Bake 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large container.
Cover and refrigerate overnight (or at least 2 1/2 hours).
Remove shrimp from marinade and layer in a shallow pan.
Bake at 350°, just until shrimp turn pink.
Makes 24 hors d'oeuvres.

title: texas chocolate pecan pie
directions: In boiler, add sugar, milk, eggs, flour, vanilla, chocolate and pecans.
Bake pie shell according to directions.
Stir ingredients until mixture is thickened.
Add the pecans and stir. Pour into shell.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Pick
pie
shell with fork.
Saute onions in butter and place in pie shell.
Mix other ingredients together, excluding hot bacon and
place
over onions.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with bacon and serve with cold fruit.

title: chinese rice casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into tightly covered casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: molasses cutouts
directions: Instead of all those separate spices, I use 2 teaspoons pumpkin spice.
After mixing, cover and refrigerate overnight. Take chunks of dough.
Roll out on lightly floured board until 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen on a greased cookie sheet, 12 minutes chewy and 14 minutes crunchy.

title: mashed potato donuts
directions: Work this until you can roll it.
Roll to 3/8-inch (1/2-inch is too big).
Cut it out with a water glass.
To make the hole, use a bottle neck if you don't have anything else!
Deep fry until brown.
Let cool.
Put in bag with sugar or combination of sugar and cinnamon and shake.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Reserve 1 cup pecans.
Blend remaining ingredients with the softened cream cheese.
Chill mixture, then shape into a ball. Roll cheese ball in remaining 1 cup pecans.

title: smoked brisket
directions: Pour liquid smoke over whole brisket.
Liberally season with salts and cover with chopped onion.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before cooking, pour off liquid smoke and douse with Worcestershire sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Uncover and pour the barbecue sauce over the brisket; bake 1 more hour.

title: creamy cottage cheese dip
directions: Combine cottage cheese, mayonnaise and salad-spice-and-herb mix.
Blend in blender or with electric mixer until almost smooth. Chill.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with celery and carrot sticks.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate dipped pretzels
directions: Melt chocolate.
Dip pretzels and lay on waxed paper at room temperature.
Enjoy!
May also use strawberry or whatever you like.

title: mystery meat loaf
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and shape into mini loaves.
In a saucepan combine next 4 ingredients.
Heat until the cranberry sauce has melted.
Pour over the loaves and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven-baked herb potatoes
directions: Slice the potatoes about 1/4 inch thick.
Brush the slices with the vegetable oil.
Place in a baking pan; sprinkle with the thyme and oregano.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: floating island
directions: Add well-beaten yolks to hot milk; mix well.
Place
in top part
of double boiler.
Cook until liquid	coats
spoon. Cool quickly and add salt and artificial sweetener.
Beat
egg whites until stiff.
Add 4 tablespoons of powdered
sugar, one at	a time,
beating after each addition. Pour
custard
into dessert dishes.
Put
egg whites on top of each.
Garnish with your favorite jam, jelly or fruit.

title: hot sausage rolls
directions: Cook sausage and crumble. Grate cheese in a large bowl. Add sausage. Let stand at room temperature 1/2 to 1 hour. Add 2 cups Bisquick. Mix like pie dough until well blended. Make into walnut size balls. Place on lightly greased cookie sheets. Press down gently with fork tines. Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes. Check frequently. Let tops get light tan. Drain on paper towels. Also freezes well. Makes 48 to 60 balls.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
Do not open oven door until time is up.

title: bacon cheese appetizers
directions: Mix; spread on party rye and broil until bubbly.

title: pumpkin crumble
directions: Mix together sugar, pumpkin spice, eggs, pumpkin and evaporated milk. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Sprinkle box of yellow cake mix over the pumpkin layer.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and drizzle over the cake mix.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup chopped pecans over all this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: best chili ever
directions: In Dutch oven, cook beef, onion, green pepper and celery until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Add chopped tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add kidney beans the last 20 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage; steam long enough to make leaves flexible. Separate leaves and cool.
In large bowl, combine meat, rice, onion, pepper, garlic, celery, 1 can stewed tomatoes, 1 can tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Blend.
Place 1 spoon of mixture on cabbage leaf; roll up like a tamale and place in a 5-quart pot. When finished making rolls, top with remaining can of stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce plus 2 cans water.
Cover; bring to boil and turn down heat to simmer and simmer 2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: frosting
directions: Cook pudding in milk; allow to cool.
Put plastic wrap over pudding to prevent a skin as it cools.
Beat the pudding, margarine and Crisco until light.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Frosts a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk and yeast mixture.
Knead.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut into biscuits.
Let stand approximately 15 minutes to rise.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes. This dough keeps well in refrigerator up to 3 days, if kept in covered dish.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter or margarine over high heat.
Add oysters, water, salt, celery salt and paprika.
Cook until oysters begin to curl at edges.
Add milk.
When mixture reaches boiling point, remove from heat.
Serve at once.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Parboil and peel shrimp.
Mix margarine with onions, celery and bell pepper in heavy pot.
Cook uncovered over medium heat until onions are wilted.
Add catsup and shrimp.
Dissolve cornstarch or flour with cold water to make paste.
Add to shrimp stirring constantly.
Season to taste with salt, black pepper and red pepper.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Mix well.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: creamy cabbage slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and sliced onions.
Blend together mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, celery seed and salt, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Toss together mayonnaise mixture and cabbage until well blended.

title: garlic roasted potato wedges
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Cut each half to four wedges.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, eggs, butter and pecans (pecans finely chopped).
Pour into crust and bake for about an hour at 275°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Combine flour, soda and baking powder. With an electric mixer at medium-low speed, beat butter and peanut butter until smooth and creamy. Beat in granulated and brown sugar and the vanilla. Beat in egg.
Reduce speed to low and beat in flour mixture. Roll dough into approximately 1-inch balls and put about 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using fork dipped in flour, press crisscross pattern into each ball to flatten it. Bake until edges just start to brown, about 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: steak strip creole
directions: Cook in crock-pot.
Cook steak strips about 2 hours.
Mix all ingredients together with steak strips.
Cook on high for 4 to 5 hours.
Turn on low for 3 to 4 hours until tender.
Put in okra when turned on low.

title: navy beans
directions: Wash beans and pick dirt or rocks out.
Place beans in cooker or bean pot in water to cover.
Cook slowly.
Add ham hock, onion (cut up), garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until beans are soft.
Be sure to keep water in pot.
Serve with corn bread.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix everything together. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or sliced bagels.

title: wedding cookies
directions: In medium bowl with mixer at medium speed, cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and flour; continue beating until well mixed.
Stir in nuts.
Cover.
Chill dough for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter in a large bowl. Mix together.
Cook sugar and milk until it reaches soft ball stage (about 12 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pour into the peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme mixture.
Mix until creamy.
Pour into a greased pan.
Let cool.

title: mint inside cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt. Set aside. Cream together butter and sugars. Add eggs, water and vanilla. Then add the flour mixture. Mix until well blended. Chill dough (works much better when chilled). Take dough and roll into a ball. Then place the mint inside of ball, then flatten it. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool, then enjoy.

title: pasta marinara
directions: Saute lightly the garlic in olive oil.
Slowly add tomatoes and puree; stir in spices and choice of vegetables.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve over 1 pound of your favorite cooked pasta.

title: batter for shrimp and vegetables
directions: Sift together first 4
ingredients.
Add egg, water and oil. Beat until smooth.	Dip
shrimp
or vegetables in batter and fry in deep hot oil.
Will
keep
in
refrigerator
for at least a week.

title: hush puppies
directions: Stir together to mix thoroughly the flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and garlic powder.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoonfuls into deep hot fat (375°).
Cook, turning frequently, about 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: black-eyed peas and ham casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Mix ham and black-eyed peas (with juice) and salt and pepper to taste.
Add rice and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with corn-on-the-cob, bread and tomatoes.

title: apple torte--combine
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well, then take 1 cup out for topping. Put the remaining mix into 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Fill with fruit of choice, about 2 cups will do.
(Use any type of fruit filling you want here.
I have used blackberries, raspberries, huckleberries, peaches, blueberries and cherries.)
Mix remaining ingredients in a separate saucepan on stove.
Boil until clear. Pour over fruit.
Add topping.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: lite blt pasta salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; toss gently. Combine mayo and next 6 ingredients; stir well. Add dressing to salad. Toss gently. Serve immediately. Yields 10 servings.

title: nippy nachos
directions: Arrange chips on large waxed paper-lined glass plate.
Sprinkle taco sauce over chips according to taste.
Sprinkle cheeses over chips evenly.
Top each chip with olive slice.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Rotate dish on High for 1 to 2 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Serve hot.
Yield:
20 nachos.

title: "country baked hash"
directions: Combine meat, potatoes, green pepper and salt into buttered casserole.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk and cook until smooth.
Stir in soup mixture and blend.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: company corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine in skillet until lightly browned. Combine all ingredients except cheese and paprika in bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes. Cover top thickly with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: party recipe fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add beaten eggs and flour.
Set aside.
Mix all fruits and nuts (chopped) together.
Mix fruit mixture with other ingredients.
Use hands to mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
If mixture begins to stick to hands, rinse in cold water.

title: pork and bean casserole
directions: After cooking bacon, saute together with onion, then add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Dust with cheese on top.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into florets and arrange in long dish.
Chop one large onion, mixing with broccoli.
Let set for several hours. Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over broccoli and onions. Top with crumbled bacon and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: easy chicken
directions: Place rice in bottom of baking pan with a lid.
Place chicken pieces on top of uncooked rice.
Pour mushroom soup on top of chicken.
Cover rice and chicken with liquid.
Season to taste. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 10.
Takes 5 minutes to prepare.

title: old fashion peanut butter cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift baking powder, salt and flour.
Slowly add flour and milk alternately to egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake at 350°.
(Needs to be thin layers, 8 to 10.)

title: rice-a-roni casserole
directions: Cook rice according to instructions on box; cook 15 minutes. Add remaining ingredients which have been chopped.
Include juice from artichoke hearts.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 20 minutes or in microwave to warm.
This is also good cold as a salad.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan the flour, oleo and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Watch carefully!! Cool.

title: crabmeat toasties
directions: Blend cheese and margarine.
Add mayonnaise and spices.
Stir in crabmeat.
Spread on English muffin halves, cut into quarters (8 pieces per muffin).
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar gradually; cream mixture until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs.
Pour boiling water over cocoa.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Combine the milk and add vanilla and add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Mix cornstarch with cheese.
