In a 4 to 6-quart pot, bring water to a boil.
Add cheese mixture a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook over medium heat, stirring until cheese melts and mixture becomes smooth.
Remove from heat and add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.

title: sarah's momma's simple chili
directions: In large frying pan, brown ground beef and drain grease.
Add all remaining ingredients to drained ground beef.
Bring to a boil stirring occasionally.
Cover and simmer for 10 - 15 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal, soda and salt.
Mix until blended. Add chocolate chips and M&M's.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix together and pour over vanilla wafers.

title: mama's pecan pie
directions: Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes, then at 300°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot tuna sandwich
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Butter one side of each slice.
Grease pan, 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place 4 slices buttered side down.
Flake tuna or salmon or ham over bread.
Add celery, onion and 1 slice of cheese on each slice of bread.
Place bread buttered side up.
Pour eggs beaten with milk over sandwiches.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
For larger pan (9 x 13-inch), increase egg mixture (1 egg and 1/2 cup milk) and 12 slices of bread.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: applesauce raisin cookies(diabetic)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix raisins, applesauce, oil, egg, vanilla and sweetener.
Add together.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: dakota potato topper
directions: In a small bowl, combine bacon bits, yogurt and horseradish. Cover. Chill until ready to serve. To serve, spoon onto baked potato halves.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Take 3/4 cup of water and 1 cup of macoroni and put it in a bowl.
Put the macoroni and water in a microwave and heat for 4 minutes.
After 4 minutes put the 1 cup of cheese in with the macoroni.
Mix that together and let cool.
After cooled, eat and enjoy.

title: pineapple-lemonade punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large plastic container.
Cover, chill and serve.
Shake well before serving.
This will make at least two gallons of punch.
More or less water can be used, depending on desired sweetness.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet and add flour.
Stir constantly until dark brown, being careful not to burn.
Reduce heat and add onion and celery.
Saute until soft.
Gradually add 2 to 3 quarts of water and seasonings; stir until smooth.
Simmer until onion and celery are well done.
Add shrimp, crab meat and green onion and cook over low heat until shrimp are tender.
Add oysters just before serving and heat until oysters curl.
Serve over rice.
If okra is used, saute with onions and celery.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: In a trifle bowl (or large bowl) continually layer cake cubes (drizzle with little Kahlua - optional), pudding and Cool Whip. You should make at least 2 layers of each. Top with sprinkles or shaved chocolate.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine sugar, butter, and oil; beat well. Add egg yolks, one at a time; beat well. Sift flour and soda together; add with buttermilk to the batter. Add vanilla, coconut, and nuts. Fold in beaten egg whites. Grease and flour 3-9 inch.
cake pans. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: honey carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain; reserve 1/4 cup of carrot liquid.
Combine reserved liquid, honey, butter and brown sugar. Stir well and pour over carrots.
Cook over low heat until heated thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Prepare cider using a large automatic coffee maker. Substitute the cider for the water.
Place remaining ingredients in coffee basket and brew.
It's delicious and the aroma is wonderful!

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in softened butter.
Stir in walnuts and Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: mr. martone's pasta sauce
directions: Process the can of tomatoes and strain through a ricer into a 6-quart saucepan.
Add tomato paste, 1 tablespoon salt, pepper and parsley.
Cook at medium heat.
Put olive oil in skillet; be sure to cover the bottom.
Saute garlic and cut sausage into links and brown.
Place sausage into the sauce.
Put the ground round into a bowl.
Add egg, bread crumbs, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Also, grate Romano cheese to taste.
Form ground round into meatballs and brown.
After browning, add meatballs to the sauce.
Strain a small amount of pan drippings into the sauce. Cook for about 3 hours.

title: french cabbage soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine vegetable juice, broth and dry onion soup mix.
Add celery, cabbage and onion.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: asparagus rice bake
directions: Put rice, soup, water and Cheddar cheese into a baking dish. Mix well.
Layer American cheese across the top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot.
Serves 5.

title: chili pie
directions: Layer 2 cups corn chips, onion, 1/2 cup cheese and chili in a 1-quart casserole.
Top with remaining corn chips.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: maple applesauce muffins
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add maple syrup.
Stir in eggs and applesauce.
Stir in flour mixture.
Bake in muffin tin at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: salmon salad
directions: Drain salmon and remove small boxes.
Break into pieces.
Add eggs, onions and 2 tablespoons relish.
Mix well.
Add Miracle Whip and mix.
Gently stir in tomatoes.
Chill and serve as sandwich or with crackers.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt butter and combine with graham cracker crumbs.
Press into 8 x 10-inch glass dish.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Pour into dish.
Let set until firm.
Layer remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: jam and cheese loaf
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand for 5 minutes. Add biscuit mix, 1 tablespoon sugar and eggs; stir well.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic. Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top; cover and chill for 8 hours.
Punch dough down; turn out on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Roll into a 14 x 9-inch rectangle.

title: nacho favorite casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Put into microwave-safe bowl with cover.
Add onion, tomato sauce, water, chili powder, kidney beans and taco sauce.
Cook about 10 minutes, but check at 5 minutes.
Make sure beans are cooked.
Great served over rice.
After mixture is done, serve.
Add fresh tomatoes, lettuce and cheese and serve tortilla chips on plate.
We like dipping chips in mixture.
Fast and easy!

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender. Add butter and mayonnaise. Mash all this together. Add remaining ingredients, except cracker crumbs. Pour into baking dish. Top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: paul revere bread
directions: Grease bottom of 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool bread 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Can be served warm or cooled.

title: steak delight
directions: Cut steak into 4 x 6-inch pieces.
Spread mustard over steak and add 3 quartered carrots, 1 pickle and 1 spoon of onions.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Brown steak in oil.
Add mushroom soup and celery and cook well done.

title: sue's wonder biscuits
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Add the 1/2 cup lard and work together as for pie crust.
In a 1-cup measure, lightly beat egg and add enough milk to fill cup.
Work into flour mix with a fork, then place in refrigerator to chill.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Salt and pepper both sides and coat with flour.
In 12-inch skillet on medium-high heat, add 1/4 cup olive oil and 2 tablespoons butter.
Lightly brown both sides of chicken.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add 1 cup of water, bouillon cube, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 cup of dry wine.
Return chicken to skillet and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add juice from lemon and slice lemon over chicken; cook for 1 more minute and serve.

title: corn chowder
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes; chop onions and fry bacon.
Saute onions until soft.
Add potatoes and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes are soft (about 15 minutes).
In a small pan, warm the half and half.
Add to chowder; crumble bacon and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Place berries in a bowl and toss with sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, lemon and vanilla. Spoon berries into a chilled crust. Add top crust and seal. Split with own design. Brush with water or egg white for brownness. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 400°.

title: crescent dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let set for 10 minutes. Combine the sugar, milk, oil, salt and eggs.
Add the flour with baking soda.
Add the yeast.
Cover the bowl and let it stand on the counter overnight.
Remove from bowl to a floured surface and knead.
Divide in half and roll out two 9 inch circles.
Cut each circle into 12 wedges.
Roll up into crescents starting at widest edge.
Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: hogshead cheese
directions: Cut hog's head into 4 pieces; remove eyes, brains, and tissue.
Put all meat into a large pot.
Cover with water and boil until meat falls from bones.
Remove meat and chop.
Then season to taste with seasonings listed.

title: cantaloupe waldorf salad
directions: Wash and cut grapes in half.
Mix fruit and nuts together in a bowl.
Refrigerate.
Serve in crisp iceberg lettuce cups.
Top with Cream Cheese Dressing (recipe follows).
Serves 9.

title: buckaroo beans
directions: Cook beans in boiling water for 2 minutes; remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Return to heat; add onions, garlic, bay leaves and salt pork.
Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients except salt.
Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat to simmer and cook for 2 more hours.
Salt to taste.

title: quick cheese straws
directions: Roll 1/8-inch thick; sprinkle with paprika.
Cut into three-inch strips and bake 8 to 10 minutes in 400° oven.
A perfect holiday snack with drinks or soups or salads.

title: christmas jewel cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix shortening, sugar, molasses and egg. Stir dry ingredients together; blend into shortening mixture. Stir in fruit and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonful about 1 inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: water chestnuts and bacon
directions: Wrap the water chestnuts in bacon and secure with toothpick. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Drain fat.
Mix the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over the water chestnuts. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add orange sherbet.
Add remaining liquid. Stir and chill until set. Whip the cream and fold into jello. Add mandarin oranges. Top with thin layer of Cool Whip.

title: never fail pot roast(easy)
directions: In heavy, covered Dutch oven, place rump roast.
Add dry onion soup mix and 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
Mix in enough water to almost cover meat.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Kisses.
Shape dough into balls, using a round teaspoonful for each.
Roll balls in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately while warm with a candy Kiss.
Press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.

title: chicken chow mein casserole
directions: Mix all together. Place in 2-quart buttered casserole, adding noodles last. Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: fried beaver
directions: Cut beaver into serving size portions.
Remove fat and boil until tender.
Drain, season with salt and pepper.
Fry with bacon slices.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add milk.
Stir to mix well. Cook on top of stove until it starts to thicken.
Add butter. Cook on low heat until desired thickness.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
In large microwave-safe bowl, combine chili, tomato paste, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and browned ground beef.
Microwave on High (100%) power for 6 to 8 minutes or until heated through and flavors are blended.

title: zucchini hors d'oeuvres
directions: Combine all ingredients, except zucchini.
Mix well.
Stir in zucchini.
Spread evenly in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve warm. Yields about 4 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, mustard and salt together. Stir in bread.
Add sausage and cheese.
Pour mixture in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hilde's sour cream tuna casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 7 ingredients. Stir well and add well-drained tuna. Add cooked noodles and mix well. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and top with cheese. Top with breadcrumbs. Extra dots of butter can be added on top of crumbs. Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Boil macaroni according to directions on box.
Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet.
Then add tomatoes, paprika, chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Drain macaroni.
Add sauce to macaroni and add garlic salt to taste.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix together; put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: rigatoni casserole(kids fav)
directions: While cooking noodles according to package directions, cut up Smokies and shred cheeses.
Drain noodles and add all ingredients to a 9 x 13-inch or larger pan and stir.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Mix ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields a 2-quart casserole.
This is good with any kind of chicken.

title: crispy chicken rolls
directions: Cook and dice shrimp; set aside.
On cutting board, with mallet, pound chicken pieces to about 1/4-inch thickness.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Layer chicken, chipped beef and bacon in that order in a lasagna pan (or deep 9 x 13-inch pan).
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt and mustard.
Add milk; heat, stirring constantly until sauce thickens slightly.
Add cheese; heat until melted.
Boil macaroni 6 minutes; drain.
Combine sauce and macaroni in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Scald milk and add sugar, salt, butter, nutmeg and potatoes. Beat until fluffy.
Beat egg yolks and add to sweet potato mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into potatoes and pour into a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until firm.
Top with marshmallows.
Brown in oven.
Serves 8.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add oil, coffee and milk; mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans (or two 8-inch pans and 6 muffin cups).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover with favorite icing.

title: snicker doodles
directions: Preheat oven at 375°. In a large bowl cream the butter until light. Add the eggs and beat until mixture in smooth. Add milk and continue to beat until the dough begins to form. Combine sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl. Roll the mixture into 1 inch balls and roll in sugar and cinnamon blend. Arrange on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes, then place on rack to cool.

title: best salmon spread
directions: Mix salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt and liquid smoke.
Chill for several hours.
Combine nuts and parsley.
Shape salmon mixture in fish shape.
Roll salmon on wax paper into nut, parsley mixture until covered.
Decorate with green olive for the eye and celery leaves for fins.
Serve with cocktail rye.

title: beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir just enough to mix spices.
Cover and let set to low for 10 to 12 hours or high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: fruit punch
directions: Blenderize oranges, lemons and slightly thawed strawberries. Pour blenderized fruit into Kool-Aid mixture.
Stir well.
Then pour punch through strainer to remove small particles.
Chill. Mix ginger ale with punch before serving.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Chop or grate onion, radishes, cucumber, pepper, celery and carrot finely.
The amount you chop of each of these will be to your taste (a little of this, a lot of that).
After boiling eggs, let cool.
Then chop finely.
Add pickle relish and mustard.
Add enough mayonnaise to get the consistency you desire.
(I prefer it to be a little soupy.)
Salt and pepper to taste.
Blend all these ingredients well and then chill.
Make your macaroni according to package directions.
Add your mayonnaise mixture to macaroni. Blend well.
Garnish with paprika or tomatoes.
Chill.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Milk will make mixing easier.

title: coffee drops
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add eggs, molasses, soda, coffee and spices; mix well.
Stir in flour, raisins and nuts.
Blend well and drop on well-greased sheet pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Bake at 375°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, sour cream, cheese, soup and salt and pepper together.
Spread smoothly in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour over with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly in center.

title: creole corn(fresh-like)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: savory herbs
directions: Combine and mix well; makes 1/2 cup. Omit or add ingredients to suit personal taste. Use in place of seasoning salt to flavor soups, meats and vegetables.

title: good cookies
directions: Mix together well.
Drop by spoonfuls and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: m.y.f. classic lemonade(worden united methodist church)
directions: Put lemon and sugar in a quart jar.
Use a new hammer handle to mash lemon and sugar together.
Pour ice and water from cup to jar.
Cover with lid and shake well or until sugar is free from bottom.
Pour mixture back into 16 ounce cup.
Enjoy!

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour in crust.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate, peanut butter and butter together. Pour over cereal. Mix well. Add sugar and cover. Shake well after adding sugar.

title: pork hawaiian
directions: In a medium saucepan, measure 2 cups water and salt; boil. When water boils, measure rice and add to the water and then cover pan with a lid.
Turn heat off.

title: dream pie(makes two 9-inch pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 unbaked crusts. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Dough should not be too stiff, but stiff enough to handle.
Roll out on floured board and cut in shapes as you wish.
Bake at 350° on slightly greased cookie sheet until slightly brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: veggie rice
directions: Put oil in saucepan on medium/high heat.
Stir in vegetables and rice.
Stir 2 to 3 minutes until well coated (not brown).
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Turn to low and cover with lid.
Cook 15 minutes and then turn off stove.
Leave pot on stove eye at least 15 more minutes).
Fluff with fork and add lemon pepper to taste.

title: bread pot fondue
directions: Slice off top of bread.
Hollow out center, leaving 1/2 shell.
Combine ingredients.
Spoon filling into hollowed out loaf and replace top.
Wrap loaf tightly with 2 or 3 layers of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Set on cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; place on platter. Stir gently.
Serve with assorted raw veggies and crackers.

title: coconut and pineapple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix first 4 ingredients together and melt together on top of stove; stir until hot.
Add coconut and pineapple.
Fill 1 unbaked pie shell with mixture.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Prepare Dream Whip.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Store in refrigerator.
Serves 8.

title: tiger tempters
directions: Brown meat; drain. Cube cheese. Add remaining ingredients except bread. Simmer until cheese is melted. Stir when mixture is spreadable. Spread on rye bread. Freeze if desired on cookie sheets. Before serving, remove from freezer and put under broiler until golden and toasty on top.

title: italian zucchini and sausage
directions: Panfry crumbled sausage over medium heat for about 15 minutes. Add onion, garlic and zucchini; cook for 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings; cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until zucchini is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: cheese cake
directions: First - Crust:
Add 1 egg, oil and cake mix into bowl and mix. Save out 1 cup of batter.
Pour and spread in bottom of cake pan.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim all visible fat from meat, partially freeze (helps to slice).
Slice with the grain 1/8 to 1/4 inch wide and 4 to 12 inches long.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Mix with beef strips.
Place in glass dish, cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Lay beef strips in single layers on oven racks with cookie sheets below.
Bake at 140° for 10 to 15 hours or until they are leathery.
Blot any drops of oil from jerky.
Place in airtight container and store in refrigerator or freeze.

title: never fail fudge icing
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and corn syrup in saucepan. Cook 3 minutes.
Set pan in cold water and stir.
When bottom of pan is cool enough to put your hand on, you may add powdered sugar and vanilla.
If a thicker icing is desired, you may add 1/2 cup more of powdered sugar.

title: hot cinnamon pickles
directions: *To make cucumber rings, peel and slice cucumbers 3/8-inch thick; remove centers of each slice.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water until tender.
Drain and rinse; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: coconut-caramel dessert
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, press into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or light brown. Cool completely.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Combine above ingredients; shape into patties.
Fry in a little margarine (or use Pam) until lightly browned on each side.

title: southern spiced tea
directions: Make tea of boiling water and tea leaves.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Make syrup of sugar and water.
Add cloves.
Add this and fruit juice to hot tea.
Can be used as hot tea or cooled and served as iced tea.
Makes about 18 cups.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix well and store in container with tight lid.
To make individual cups, add boiling water to 1/4 cup dry ingredients. Fills two 3-pound coffee cans.

title: quick and easy baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni al dente.
Drain well.
Mix in 2 1/2 cans soup, leaving 1/2 can of soup for topping (or few slices of cheese). Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Place in 8 x 10 x 3-inch baking dish. Cover with aluminum sheet.
(Remove near end of cooking to brown.) Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until light brown and bubbly.

title: vinegar dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake well before using.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except 10x sugar and lemon juice) and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Bake in tube pan (greased and floured) at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Marinate meat overnight.
Grill 8 minutes on each side.
Slice thinly, diagonally.
Will be pink when slicing but will continue to cook after it is sliced.
Serves 3 people.

title: south carolina chews
directions: Cream
margarine and sugar together.
Add vanilla, then eggs and beat well with mixer.
Mix nuts with flour and add to the mixture
last.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° in large baking pan.
Let cool in pan.
Cut into squares.

title: fran's rolled chicken breast
directions: Pound chicken breasts and add chopped spinach.
Roll tight and put a toothpick to hold.
Brown in oil; add wine, pepper, onion powder and garlic and saute about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: batter fried fish
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Drop in the egg yolk.
Add water and shortening.
Mix.
Fold in beaten egg white. Drop fish in the batter and fry in oil 4 to 6 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Add sugar and flour to medium saucepan over medium heat; add salt.
Mix milk and eggs; beat.
Add to sugar, flour and salt. Cook until it starts to boil.
Add cocoa and butter.
Cook until thick (mixture will thicken while it cools).
Take off stove and add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell. Make meringue and spread on top. Bake for about 3 minutes or until golden brown.

title: special pork chops
directions: In an ovenproof skillet, brown the pork chops in oil; drain any fat.
Pour salsa over chops.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: chili con queso - meat dip
directions: Brown and drain meat and sausage.
Add jalapeno peppers and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted and ingredients are well mixed.
Serve with tortilla or other corn chips.

title: baked fish
directions: Rinse fish and dry with paper towel. Brush fish with olive oil. Salt and pepper both sides of the fish and place on a baking dish. Rub the top of the fish with the fresh garlic and sprinkle the fish with herbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with your favorite side dishes. (I like to slice a lime and squeeze on my fish.) Makes 2 servings.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Pour into a large bowl 2 cups boiling water, jello, blueberry pie filling and pineapple.
Stir until jello dissolves.
Pour into a rectangular Pyrex.
Put into refrigerator until congealed.
Blend other ingredients until creamed.
When congealed mixture is firm, spread on creamed topping.

title: chicken and almond casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips, tossing lightly with fork.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: english muffin loaf
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, active dry yeast, sugar, salt and soda. Heat milk and water to 120°. Add to dry mixture and beat well. Stir in the remaining flour to make a stiff batter. Spoon batter into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans that have been well-greased and sprinkled with corn meal. Sprinkle the tops of the loaves with more corn meal. Cover loaves with a tea-towel and allow to rise in a warm place, free from draft, for 45 minutes. Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes. Remove from pans immediately and cool on rack. Makes 2 loaves.

title: rocks
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Add spices and salt.
Add flour and hot water.
Mix well.
Add nuts and mix by hand.
Drop from spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix together, drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until almost done.
Let finish on hot cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen small cookies.

title: surprise packages
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: clam chowder("new england style")
directions: Saute bacon until
almost
crisp
and chop into pieces; add onion and cook
for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper and 2 cups of water.
Cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain	clams,	saving	one
cup
of clam liquid, then add clams, butter, half and half and clam liquid; mix and let cook on low until desired thickness.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Spread broccoli in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan, mix Miracle Whip, cubed Velveeta cheese, lemon juice and soup.
Heat, stirring, until cheese melts.
Add chicken.
Spread mixture over broccoli.
Mix margarine and crackers; spread over casserole. Bake 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tea cake dough
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and shortening, then add vanilla and flour. Roll out on floured paper; cut in desired shapes.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Can be used to make layers for stack cake.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican sandwiches
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain.
Add remaining ingredients except rolls.
Pinch bread out of center of rolls; fill with beef mixture.
Wrap each roll in foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's potato soup
directions: Or add ingredients as desired.
Cut potato, onion and celery in small pieces.
Cook in scant amount of water.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.
When potatoes are cooked thoroughly, stir or mash to help thicken.
Add milk, salt and pepper to taste.
(After adding milk, heat but do not boil.)

title: mincemeat bars
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients well.
Place half of the mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Fill with mincemeat, apples and almond paste.
Cover this with the rest of the mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes and cool.
Mix fruit in blender. Combine sugar and water mixture with fruit mixture and mix well. Add lemon, orange and pineapple juices.
Stir well and divide. Makes 2 (1/2 gallon) milk cartons full.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer at least 4 hours before serving.

title: chuck roast stew
directions: Cut meat and vegetables and layer in ovenproof pan.
Mix mushroom soup, onion soup mix and water together.
Spread over meat and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for about 3 hours.
Stir after 2 hours.

title: chicken squares
directions: Stew chicken breasts.
Cut in small pieces after deboning. Blend cream cheese with margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onion.
Mix well.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Place butter and 2/3 cup cream in a heavy pan, bring to a boil and simmer 1 minute until slightly thickened.
Bring a pan of salted water to a boil; cook the fettuccine according to the package directions.
The pasta should be firm or al dente.
Drain the pasta through and turn into the pan with the cream sauce. Turn the pasta in the sauce to coat evenly.
Add the remaining cream, cheese, salt and pepper to taste and a little ground nutmeg.
Toss until well coated and heated through.
Serve immediately with some extra grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: rye chip appetizers
directions: Note:
May substitute Mozzarella cheese (or use both).

title: karen's bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve in middle of pumpernickel or rye bread.
Use both, breaking up chunks.

title: salmon pate
directions: Line a 2-cup bowl or small pan with plastic wrap.
Blend salmon, Good Seasons mix, cream cheese and cucumber.
Press into bowl and chill at least one hour.
Unmold, serve with crackers or cucumber slices.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine chocolate milk and Eagle Brand into electric or hand cranked ice cream mixer.
Freeze.
When finished, let stand for 10 minutes.
Tastes like a Wendy's Frosty.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together and drain. In a 9 x 13 baking pan, crumble up the Doritos and pour hamburger meat over them. Add cheese to the top. Bake in oven at 375° until cheese melts. Place other ingredients on top as desired and ready to eat.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquid slowly, then add butter. Cook until thickened.
Pour over beets and serve hot.

title: pizza dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Heat for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and 1/4 cup of sugar.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool, then cream together the cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup of sugar.
Put this on the pretzel crust when it has cooled.
Mix strawberry Jell-O according to directions on box.
Let it congeal and pour it on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: baked sausage stuffing(makes 8 servings)
directions: Cook sausage, onion and celery in skillet until meat is browned and vegetables tender.
Pour off drippings, reserving 1/4 cup.
Add melted butter or margarine, if necessary, to make 1/4 cup.
Combine bread cubes, sausage mixture, reserved drippings, salt, sage, thyme and pepper in a large bowl.
Blend together eggs and chicken broth.
Stir into bread mixture.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Uncover and continue baking 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together. This is better if chilled at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Let bread dough thaw completely.
Roll out until very thin rectangle.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and pepperoni.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for about 3 minutes or until browned and baked through. Serve warm, cut into thin slices.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Have everything ready!
Mix brown sugar, white sugar and milk together; cook for 2 minutes after rolling boil.
Beat in Marshmallow Fluff, peanut butter and then add nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool.

title: 14 day pickles
directions: Pour boiling liquid over pickles in jars.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour liquid out into large pan and bring to boil again. Refill jars and seal.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: country brunch
directions: Place 1/2 of the bread cubes in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Put 1/2 of the sausage on top, then 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt, and pepper.
Pour mixture over layers in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: puddings(using basic pudding mix)
directions: In top part of double boiler, combine mix and 2 1/2 cups warm water.
Put over boiling water and cook, stirring once or twice, for 10 minutes.
Add butter and remove from heat.
With spoon, beat half the mixture into egg, then stir into mixture in double boiler.
Cook, stirring, over hot (not boiling) water for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Cool, stirring once or twice, then chill.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Let set while you prepare remaining ingredients: cream cheese, mayonnaise and salt.
Fold into jello along with nuts, pineapple and cherries.

title: carli's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
You may dip in sugar before flattening, if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry tart
directions: In 1 cup water cook 1 cup small blueberries (thawed if using frozen blueberries) until smooth; strain out seeds to make smooth. Mix cornstarch and cold water; add this to berry mixture.
Next, add sugar.
Cook in saucepan until thickened; allow to cool.
When cooled, add 4 cups blueberries (thawed if using frozen ones).
Mix well and fold into baked pie shell and serve.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and chopped olives.
Then spread on each ham slice.
Now roll ham slice, starting with shorter side (may secure with a toothpick).
Chill rolls overnight.
Slice into about 1/4-inch wide pieces.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix salmon (juice and all) with flour.
You may need more flour, it's up to you.
Shape into patties and roll in self-rising corn meal.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Yellow corn meal is better.
Fry in oil; turn and brown on both sides.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown meat, 1/2 chopped onion and 1 clove garlic over medium-high heat, stirring often to break up lumps of meat.
Stir in refried beans.
Transfer mixture to a medium bowl and set aside.
In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium heat.
Add remaining onion and cook, stirring often, until softened, about 3 minutes.
Add remaining garlic jalapeno pepper, chili powder and cumin.
Cook, stirring, 30 seconds.
Stir in tomato sauce and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer partially covered, until sauce is slightly thickened, about 20 minutes.
Stir 1/2 cup sauce into meat-bean mixture.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil noodles as directed on package.
Meanwhile, steam broccoli, if desired. Chop green onions and cucumber.
When noodles are done, drain and run cool water over.
Place noodles in large bowl.
Combine other ingredients and bacon bits as desired. Toss with choice of dressing.

title: japanese mandarin orange dessert
directions: Drain juice from oranges.
Add enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Bring to a boil.
Dissolve lemon jello into hot liquid. Add 1 cup cold water; cool until syrupy.
Line spring-form pan with ladyfingers (bottom and sides).
Fold syrupy mixture into whipped cream.
Add oranges (save some oranges to decorate top). Fill lined spring-form pan with mixture.
Chill overnight.
Serves at least 10.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on, cool, peel and grate.

Heat soup and butter. Blend in sour cream. Layer in 9 x 11 buttered baking dish three times with potatoes, onions, cheese and sauce, ending with sauce.	Sprinkle top with crumbs; dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sparkling ginger fruit punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine pineapple juice, orange juice and ginger ale.
Add ice before serving.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large saucepan cook onions in butter covered for 20 minutes or until tender.
Add condensed beef broth, worcestershire sauce, 1/4 tsp. salt and a dash of pepper; bring to a boil.
Ladle soup into broiler proof soup bowls, place a bread slice on soup; sprinkle with cheese.
Broil until cheese is golden brown.
Make 6-8 servings.

title: baked bar-b-q meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, milk, salt, cracker crumbs and onion.
Make into meatballs.
Put in 9 x 13 pan (shallow pan).
Mix together catsup, vinegar and brown sugar.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sandy's salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Cook puddings, using fruit juice, adding water and juice to make 3 cups.
Cool; add fruit.
Chill.
Can be made day before serving.

title: hurry up fruit cake
directions: Warm all ingredients to warm temperature.
Line greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with waxed paper.
Paper needs to extend 1/2 inch above all sides of pan.
Grease paper.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with pie crust. Fill with apples.
Add sugar and cinnamon.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and margarine.
Put on low or medium heat and stir constantly until boils.
After coming to a rolling boil, boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly (as this mixture scorches easily).
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips and stir until melted.
Then add marshmallows, nuts and vanilla.
Mix all together well and pour on platter.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Coat the inside of a large Dutch oven with nonstick cooking spray.
Saute onion and apple until tender.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until tender, about 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: sundance eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wrap tortillas in foil; bake about 5 minutes until warm.
Combine eggs, water and salt in a medium bowl; beat well.
In a large skillet melt butter; add eggs and scramble until set.
Remove from heat; place warm tortillas on a large, ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each tortilla with 1/4 of eggs, onion, tomatoes, chilies and cheese.
Bake for 5 to 10 minutes until cheese is melted.
Top each with 1 tablespoon taco sauce and sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spicy roasted tomato soup
directions: Bring the chicken stock to a boil in a stockpot. Add the onions, 4 red peppers, tomatoes, garlic and carrots. Cook until the vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally. Season with the curry powder, salt and pepper. Pour into a blender container. Process until pured. Ladle into soup bowls. Top each serving with sliced roasted peppers.

title: ruby wine punch
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, water and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Strain out spices and chill the liquid.
Chill the wine and fruit juice.
Combine thoroughly the chilled liquids when ready to serve.
Makes 12 to 14 (4 ounce) servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine apple slices and 1/2 cup sugar in bottom of 2 quart casserole.
Mix butter, oats, flour, 1/2 cup sugar and nuts. Sprinkle butter and oats mixture over apples.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour, until topping is brown and apples are tender.
Serve warm.
May be topped with ice cream.

title: seven up cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add lemon extract.
Alternate flour and 7-Up.
Mix well.
Pour into tube pan or 2 loaf pans.

title: seashell pirohi
directions: Cook shells as package directs.
Drain.
Rinse; drain again. Mash potatoes.
Add cheese and 1/2 cup butter.
When cool, add eggs, salt and pepper.
Fill shells with the potato mixture and arrange in a single layer in baking dish.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and flour in medium size saucepan. Mix well. Add egg yolks, milk and butter. Stir all up good. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat after the mixture thickens and pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook until done. Top with meringue.

title: meat loaf dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serve with bread warmed in oven or hot rolls and a tossed salad with a light dessert.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put in pie shell and chill overnight.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar and molasses together in saucepan. Boil for 5 minutes.

title: virgie's salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water; let cool.
Cream the cream cheese with mixer, add the other ingredients.
Pour in dish and chill.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles and cut in 1-inch cubes.
Soak in sugar and vinegar 4 hours at room temperature, stirring occasionally.
Put in jar with spice sack and cinnamon stick and refrigerate one week before eating.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light.
Add oil and vanilla and mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add pineapple, carrots and 1 cup chopped nuts (optional) and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Mix together confectioners sugar, butter, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread on cake when cool.

title: icing
directions: Boil oleo, cocoa and milk.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and walnuts.
Keep on low heat while frosting cake.

title: pink punch
directions: Do not dilute lemonade.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add sugar, then mix with other liquids.
Chill thoroughly.
Make a frozen mold from some of the punch mix and place in punch bowl when serving.

title: chew bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla. Fold in pecans.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in 2 cups water, until done.
Do not drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and butter to taste.

title: mrs. murphy's fish chowder
directions: Fry 4 slices bacon in large frypan until crisp.
Remove bacon and add onion and potatoes and fry for a short time. Add water to cover potatoes and lay fish on top of potatoes. Cook until fish turns white and solid (15 minutes).

title: oatmeal icebox cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Slice thin.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: nut kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Beat in sugar.
Fold in vanilla, salt and nuts.
Batter should be fluffy.
If not, beat longer.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 40 - 60 minutes.
Cookies will just barely be golden.
If you cook too long, they will taste burnt.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix together, adding milk last.
Place on heavily floured board.
Work with hands until smooth enough to roll out.
Roll out to 12 x 16-inches.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix meat, egg, onion, rice, 1/2 cup tomatoes, salt and pepper together.
Wash, stem and seed peppers.
Stuff peppers with meat and rice mixture.
Put peppers, rest of tomatoes and 1/4 cup water in large skillet with tight lid.
Cook slowly 45 minutes.
Remove peppers to platter.
Add sugar to tomatoes, turn up heat and cook until thick, stirring frequently.
Spoon sauce over peppers and serve.

title: zucchini fruit loaf
directions: Beat together the eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick and foamy.
Add the zucchini and well drained fruit of your choice. Combine the dry ingredients with nuts and raisins.
Add to the zucchini mixture.
Divide between loaf pans and bake for 1 hour. Cool in pans for 10 minutes before cooling on wire racks.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender, drain.
Stir butter into hot spaghetti, stir in beaten eggs and parmesan cheese.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a greased 16 inch pie plate.
Spread with cottage cheese.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix in order and chill.

title: bread-pumpkin
directions: Mix sugar and vegetable oil.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and water; mix.
Add pumpkin and mix.
Place in loaf pans and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Roll each chicken breast in sheet of dried beef and wrap with a slice of bacon.
Place in baking dish.
Combine soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil and bake 3 hours or more in 300° oven.
Remove foil for last half hour to brown.

title: machie's cracked sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Fold into butter sugar mixture.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, margarine and eggs. Add dry ingredients except oatmeal and chips, mix well.
Mix together oatmeal and chips, then add to rest of mixture. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together the sugar and flour.

title: pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1/3 cup Italian salad dressing.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours, then uncover and let brown; turn to brown on other side.

title: "noels" cookies
directions: Cream together margarine (or butter) and powdered sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and roll balls in more powdered sugar.

title: ann's marinated english peas
directions: Boil
sugar, vinegar and salt until sugar is dissolved. Cool and add oil, pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
Best if left in refrigerator overnight.
Drain and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine beef and rest of ingredients in a large bowl. Mix in tortilla chips and Thousand Island dressing and toss well.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in pan.
Drain excess fat.
Add soup, milk, macaroni, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook the ground beef and onion over medium heat until beef is brown and onion is soft.
Do not brown the onion.
Drain off the fat. Add the seasoned salt, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce, stirring to mix well.
Spread beef mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread mashed potatoes over meat, then top with cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kim's spicy wings
directions: Sprinkle chicken wings evenly with garlic pepper.
Bake at 450° until golden brown (or grill until brown).
Line baking pan with sliced Vidalia onions.
Arrange wings on top of onions.
Mix together melted butter, Red Hot and lemon juice.
Pour over wings and bake in oven at 250° for 20 to 30 minutes, turning once or twice to coat wings.

title: strawberry pie(like isaly's)
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cook until clear, stir occasionally.
Remove from fire.
Add strawberry gelatin and food coloring.
Cool.
Can keep in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, add strawberries and mix.
Pour into a ready-baked pie shell.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground meat and onions in margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Use a deep skillet with no-burn handle so you can use it in the oven.
When heat is sufficiently browned, remove from stove.
Add rest of ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: pear or apple pie
directions: If apples or pears lack tartness, sprinkle with 1 tablespoon lemon juice, if desired.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add sugar mixture to the sliced apples; toss to coat. Fill a pastry lined 9-inch pie plate with apple or pear mixture. Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edge.
Sprinkle some sugar atop, or brush with milk.
Cover edge of pastry with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove foil; bake for 20 to 25 minutes more, or until crust is golden.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: linguine carbonara
directions: Heat oil and butter over moderate heat.
Add bacon and cook until brown, not crisp, about 4 min.
Add garlic, wine and pepper. Simmer until the wine is reduced to 2 Tbsp., about 3 min.
Remove from the heat.
In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs, cheese and salt.
In a large
pot of boiling, salted water, cook the linguine until just about done, about 12 min.
Drain the pasta and add it to the egg and cheese mixture.
Toss quickly.
Pour the bacon mixture over the linguine.
Add the parsley and toss just until mixed.
Serve immediately with additional Parmesan.

title: joann's potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, celery, carrots, mushrooms and onion until tender.
Drain, reserving some of the water.
Return vegetables to stove and add butter, soups and velveeta cheese.
Add milk and reserved water until you get thickness you like.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add parsley and chives if desired.

title: fudge cookie salad
directions: Place buttermilk and instant pudding in a bowl and beat.
Add Cool Whip and beat. Stir in mandarin oranges with a spoon. Refrigerate. When ready to serve, add broken up cookies.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Be sure not to overmix batter.
In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in butter. Beat together eggs and milk.
Blend into mixture just enough to moisten flour. Do not overmix.
Fold in banana and chopped nuts. Spoon batter into a 12 greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and drain. Add taco seasoning, beans and enough water to make moist mixture.
Crush Tostitos and put 1/2 bag on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put meat mixture over crushed chips. Layer onion, lettuce and tomatoes over top of meat. Top with cheeses. Add remaining Tostitos over cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through and cheese is melted, approximately 35 minutes.

title: maple walnut or pecan pie
directions: Mix.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until set.
To make the Maple Walnut Pie, substitute maple flavoring for vanilla and walnuts for pecans.

title: sherbet ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in ice cream freezer can.
Finish filling with milk.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup of butter, onion, chicken soup, sour cream and cheese.
Spoon into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir remaining butter into crushed corn flakes; sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes, until brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into 1/8-inch thick strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef.
Toss and set aside.
Heat oil.
Add beef and saute over high heat until brown.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn heat up, add onion (sliced thin), peppers (cut in 1-inch squares), celery (sliced thin).
Cook until veggies are tender about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and 1 cup water.
Add to beef mixture and cook until thickened.
Add 2 tomatoes, cut in wedges.
Heat through and serve.

title: banana-mallow pie
directions: Combine 2 cups vanilla wafer crumbs and 1/2 cup Parkay margarine (melted).
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Brown onion and hamburg; drain.
Make mix of eggs, hamburg, 3 cups spaghetti sauce, cottage cheese, salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, Mozzarella cheese and water.

title: sweet potato soup
directions: Place potatoes, leeks or onions, carrots, celery and water in large kettle.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and simmer for 40 minutes.
With slotted spoon remove half of the carrots and celery and some of the firmer potato pieces and reserve.
Puree the remainder of soup until smooth.
Return to kettle and add reserved vegetables, margarine, milk, seed and tarragon.
Reheat and check seasonings.

title: ginger muffins
directions: Preheat oven.
Bake at 300° to 400° for 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients except flour and milk.
Add flour and milk alternately until mixed well.

title: cheese-topped skillet chicken
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil in 10-inch skillet.
Stir in chicken, tomatoes, rice, water and spices.
Bring to boil. Cover.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes until rice is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and green onion.
Cover until cheese is melted.
Serves 4.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits.
Put garlic cheese in hot grits.
Add eggs and enough milk to make 1 cup.
Add egg mixture to grits.
Bake in oven until browned on top at 350°.

title: deep dish apple dumplings(amish)
directions: Slice apples into a buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and milk.
Dot with butter.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: pineapple chicken and sweet potatoes
directions: Combine 2/3 cup flour, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, onion powder and pepper in large bowl. Thoroughly coat chicken in flour mixture. Place potatoes on bottom of slow cooker. Top with chicken. Combine soup, juice, mushrooms, remaining flour, sugar and orange peel in a small bowl; stir well. Pour soup mixture into slow cooker. Cover and cook on high 3 to 4 hours or low 8 to 10 hours. Serve with rice.

title: ole hot appetizer
directions: In a large pie pan, layer the first 5 ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Garnish with the green onions.
Serve hot with chips.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; add taco mix.
Mix and add the water; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cool and add the remaining ingredients.
Just before serving, mix in Doritos and add dressing.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Flour meat and put chunks in melted oleo to brown.
Put onion with this to cook.
After browned, add soup and water.
Simmer 1 hour.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all together.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake until cheese melts.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and fold in mayonnaise. Gradually add milk.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cut sausage into small pieces.
Fry until brown.
Add the water.
Combine other ingredients, except
butter, and stir into the sausage.
Grease a casserole dish and turn the mixture into it.
Dot with the butter and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: honey glazed chicken drumsticks
directions: Clean chicken, pat dry and rub with mixture of salt, garlic, ginger and soy sauce.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Broil chicken 15 minutes on each side until brown and done.
Turn frequently. Remove chicken from broiler and roll in honey.
Return to broiler for 2 minutes.

title: sparkling apple juice
directions: Combine apple juice and ginger ale.
Serve over ice.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: microwave self-icing chocolate cake
directions: Mix and pour into a 3-quart casserole with cone.
"Don't grease."
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes; cover and let stand 5 minutes, then invert on dish.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Line bottom of casserole with 1/2 of stuffing mixture.
Mix all else and pour over stuffing mixture in casserole.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 crumbs over mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: cheese pie
directions: Combine and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Make 2 nine-inch pies.
Delicious warmed over.

title: marinated b.b.q. chicken
directions: Roll pieces of chicken in flour and fry till brown.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Beat eggs, soup, nutmeg and salt until frothy; add cheese. Mix well and start adding well drained spinach until all is mixed. Butter deep baking dish and fill.
Cover top with sharp cheese of your choice.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean. Use cover when baking.

title: chicken-cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix in all other ingredients, except nuts.
Shape into ball or log and roll in nuts.
Chill.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put sausage in 9 x 13-inch dish. Cover with croutons and Cheddar cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: sausage bread
directions: Flatten one loaf of bread at a time.
Spread 1/3 of sausage over dough.
Roll up in loaf shape, sealing the ends.
Let the loaves raise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Last 2 to 3 minutes, rub top with butter and sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on each loaf.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Cook the ground beef and onion over medium heat in a pot. Stir and crumble meat until it is brown and the onion is soft. Drain off the fat, then stir in the ketchup and chili powder.
Add the water and simmer for 3 minutes.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: apple skillet cake
directions: Mix
flour,
sugar,
oil,
egg and cinnamon together in 9-inch iron skillet.
Add nuts and apples.
Bake in skillet at 350° for 40 minutes.
Real good served warm with ice cream.

title: winter fruit compote
directions: In large skillet, over high heat, combine sugar and the water. Bring to boiling, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Add pears and apples.
Return liquid to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer 3 minutes, until fruit is tender, but not mushy.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream the first five ingredients together.
Sift together flour, salt, cream tartar, and soda and add to the first part.
Add the nuts, oatmeal, corn flakes, coconut, and vanilla and mix until well blended.
Make dough into 1 inch balls, place on a greased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.
Grease sheet one time after each cooking, wipe with paper towel.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together.
Better if made a day ahead of time.

title: banana split
directions: Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan (do not bake).
In a large mixer bowl pour 2 cups of the milk and the 2 packages of pudding mix.
Beat well. Then add the 3/4 cup and beat again.
Let set until it thickens some.
Then fold in 1 cup whipped topping and spread over crumb layer.
Chill if possible for 15 minutes or so.
Then slice bananas over all as evenly as possible. Then spoon drained pineapple over all and sprinkle on nuts.
Next slice cherries or strawberries over all. You can sprinkle on toasted ground coconut, too.
Then cover with good layer of whipped topping.
Refrigerate several hours or longer.
Cut in squares or just spoon out to serve.

title: mexican-style chicken kiev
directions: Pound the chicken between pieces of waxed paper until each is about 1/4-inch thick.
Slit green chilies in half lengthwise; remove seeds, if desired, then cut into 8 equal pieces.
Cut cheese into 8 fingers, about 1/2-inch thick and 1 1/2 inches long. Also combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese, chili powder, garlic salt, cumin and pepper.

title: squash muffins
directions: Cook, drain and mash squash to the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Cream sugar, molasses and butter.
Add egg and squash and blend well.
Mix flour with soda and salt.
Beat this mixture into the squash batter.
Fold in pecans.
Fill well-greased muffin pans about half full with batter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: eggplant grill
directions: Steam the eggplant for about 8 minutes or just until it begins to soften.
While the eggplant steams, push the garlic through a garlic press, into a small bowl.
Stir in the onions and oil until well mixed.
Arrange the eggplant slices in one layer or on baking sheet coated with no-stick spray.
Brush with half of the garlic mixture.
Broil about 5 inches from the heat for about 5 minutes or until the slices begin to turn golden.
Turn, brush with the remaining oil mixture and broil until golden brown.
Serve hot. Makes 8 servings.

title: barbecue beef brisket
directions: Place meat in flat roasting pan or ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle 1 envelope soup mix over meat.
Pour chili sauce on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake in slow oven at 300° to 325° for approximately 2 hours.
Remove foil and add beer.
Continue in oven for 45 minutes or until tender, basting occasionally with sauce.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil.
Add zucchini, nuts and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in a greased and floured 11 x 17-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: boiled cake
directions: Cook sugar, water, Crisco, raisins, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg for 5 minutes on top of stove.

title: cauliflower and carrot dish
directions: Cook cauliflower, carrots, water and salt for 10 minutes, then put in baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and milk.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix soda crackers and butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Make in a ball and roll in crushed nuts.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix pineapple, flour, sugar and cheese and put in dish.
Put crushed crumbs on top. Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine zucchini, corn and peppers, then combine the oil, vinegar and spices.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. Cover and chill.
Serve in lettuce cups.

title: un-fried french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice each potato lengthwise into 1/4-inch ovals, then slice each oval lengthwise into matchsticks. Coat a baking sheet with 3 sprays of the vegetable oil cooking spray.
Combine the egg whites and Cajun spice in a bowl. Add potato sticks and mix to coat.
Pour potatoes onto the baking sheet. Spread out leaving space between.
Place sheet on bottom rack. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until fries are crispy, turning them every 6 to 8 minutes so they can brown evenly.
Serve immediately.

title: veal piccata
directions: Dip veal in flour.
Brown on both sides over high heat.
Add salt and pepper and cook for 5 minutes.
Shake skillet.
Add lemon juice and parsley.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir well.
Arrange on plates. Spoon sauce over veal.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Mix 2 cups of lime, into 2 gallons of water and soak cucumbers for 24 hours.
Rinse cucumbers well at least 4 times to remove all traces of lime.
Cover cucumbers with ice at least 1 to 2 inch thick layers of ice on top and let set until the ice melts.
Allow the cucumbers to drain off all excess water.

title: potato candy
directions: Use fork and mash potato fine.
Add melted margarine and vanilla.
Start mixing powdered sugar until thickens like cookie dough.
On aluminum foil, spread powdered sugar (to keep from sticking) and roll out dough to 1/4-inch thick sheet.
Spread layer of peanut butter over dough and roll into long roll.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Cool until firm.
Cut into slices.
Dust with powdered sugar until not sticky.

title: cocoa and cola cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except cola and marshmallows in large mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed for 2 minutes then blend at medium speed for 1 minute.
By hand stir in cola, blend well, then add marshmallows, blend together by hand.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 30 minutes.
Spread with icing.
Leave in pan to ice.

title: cheese fritters
directions: Place cheese in bowl and sprinkle with pepper.
Add 1/2 cup of white wine and set aside to marinate for 1 hour.

title: chocolate-coconut rice squares
directions: Combine water, sugar and salt in medium saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add chips and coconut to hot rice and stir until chips are melted.
Cover and chill.
Fold whipped topping into rice mix.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Drain artichoke hearts, reserving liquid.
Chop artichokes and set aside.
Pour artichoke liquid into a 9-inch skillet.
Add green onions and garlic and cook until tender.
Drain.
Combine eggs and pepper in a large bowl; beat mixture well.
Stir in artichokes, onion mixture, cheese, crackers and parsley.

title: easy orange blossoms
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions, adding orange flavoring to batter.
Grease and flour mini cupcake pans or spray with Baker's Joy.
Pour batter in pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until lightly brown.
While cupcakes are baking, dilute orange juice according to directions and mix with powdered sugar.
Remove cupcakes from pans immediately.
While hot, dip into orange juice and sugar mixture.
Cool.
Yields 60 to 70 mini muffins.
Great to freeze.

title: diet martinique dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a jar and refrigerate for several hours.

title: t.j. miracle soup
directions: Cut veggies in medium pieces.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes.
Turn heat down and simmer until veggies are tender.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine in saucepan the cocoa and sugar.
Blend in milk and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in butter or margarine and vanilla.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Wash and cap strawberries; peel and slice bananas in bite-size chunks.
Add pineapple and mix well.
Add strawberry glaze and coat all ingredients.
Will keep several days in refrigerator and the bananas will not turn dark.

title: potato - cheese bake
directions: Thaw frozen potatoes.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Spray a 12 x 9-inch baking pan with Pam.
Put combined ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oyster stew
directions: Place butter in saucepan and melt.
When melted, add oysters and cook until the edges begin to curl.
Add salt, pepper and milk; heat until just before a boil.
Serve with saltine crackers and for those who desire, Tabasco.

title: asado
directions: Mix all ingredients, including meat, in a stew pot.
Bring to a boil until meat is tender and leaves a nice thick gravy sauce. Take out meat and brown fry it in small amount of oil.
Cool meat and cut in thin slices.

title: cavatini
directions: Take tomato, cut the core out of the center.
Then take some rice and
bring
to
a
boil.
Let	cool,
then stuff the tomato with rice.	Add some onions, peppers and some hamburger meat cooked into
the rice mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 5 minutes at 300°.

title: applesauce cake(1925 recipe)
directions: Mix soda and spices with flour; set aside.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and beat well.
Add applesauce.
Add flour a little at a time; stir until all is blended.
Add raisins, preserves and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in electric stove or gas.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 200° for coal or wood stove.
Frost with caramel icing.

title: whole bran applesauce cake
directions: Combine bran cereal and milk; let stand until milk is absorbed.
Sift together flour, baking powder, spices, salt and soda.
Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add bran mixture, applesauce and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces using stalk and tops.
Cook bacon until crisp, crumble.
Toss dressing with all ingredients. Let set until flavors are mixed.

title: german skillet(so fast and so good.)
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in skillet or Dutch oven. Add sliced cabbage, then chopped onion, rice, uncooked meat, salt, pepper and tomato sauce. Cover with tight lid. Cook over medium heat, 35 minutes without lifting lid.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together, after cutting broccoli and cauliflower in small pieces.

title: prune nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan(s).
Measure all ingredients into a large mixer bowl; beat on medium speed 1/2 minute.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all together.
Cook 20 minutes.
Put into hot jars and seal.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Cover kraut with warm water and bring to boil; rinse with warm water, once with cold water.
Drain.

title: wilted greens with pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain well.
Keep warm.
Meanwhile, in a large serving bowl, combine spinach or romaine and green onions.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flavoring. Stir in flour and pecans.
Blend well.
Form dough into small balls.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Roll cookies in confectioners sugar while warm.

title: camp alabama corn bread dressing(from the "old green" cookbook)
directions: Cut butter into very small pieces and mix with corn bread and bread crumbs.
Heat fat in a heavy skillet; add nutmeats, celery and onion and saute slowly for 5 minutes.
Add to cornbread mixture.
Add seasonings, mixing thoroughly.
Add well beaten eggs; sprinkle cooled broth over surface, stirring lightly until dressing is of desired moistness.
Stuff lightly into breast region and body cavity of turkey.
Makes enough for a 12 pound turkey.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from the oranges and fruit cocktail; don't use.

title: italian spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill mixture before serving on bread.
Yield: 2 cups.
Delicious!!

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute vegetables.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add shrimp; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: easy pot roast
directions: In a crock-pot, place carrots, onions and meat.
Put potatoes around meat.
Mix in 2 cups of water, gravy mix and onion soup mix; stir well.
Pour over meat and veggies.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or high 4 to 5 hours.
(When you feed the dogs, share some carrots.
After all, they have smelled this cooking all day!!)

title: irene's pancake mix
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix into milk.
Add egg and beat well.
Blend in fat.
Batter will be thin.

title: apricot slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in 7 cups boiling water.
Cool.
Make tea in 2 cups boiling water.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients and put in large container (with tight lid) and freeze.
When serving, spoon into cocktail glasses.
Pour on a little ginger ale.
Serve with wedge of orange.

title: charlotte plummer gumbo
directions: In large pot, melt margarine until it foams; add flour and stir constantly over low heat until roux is light caramel color. Do not burn. Add remaining ingredients. Cook until all vegetables are soft and tender, approximately 45 minutes. Add shrimp. Continue cooking for 20 minutes. Remove from heat. Sprinkle with fil. Serve over hot fluffy rice in large bowl.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Let cool.
Chop broccoli, green onions (entire onion) and mushrooms.
Just before serving, toss veggies with dressing.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Put pineapple chunks in bowl, pour dry jello over and mix in all other ingredients.
Chill.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat potatoes and hash browns together.
Mix all ingredients except corn flakes or potato chips.
Crush corn flakes or chips and sprinkle on the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: lentil stew
directions: In stockpot combine all ingredients and simmer 45 minutes or until lentils are tender.

title: dried beef ball
directions: Blend cream cheese with horseradish.
Mold into a ring or ball.
Flake the dried beef in a blender and spread over the cream cheese.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: mrs. hitchcock's upside-down cake
directions: Put in pan or skillet brown sugar, butter and fruit.
Let boil up good and set aside while making cake batter.
Use apricots, peaches, pineapple or any good fruit.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites to peaks.
Add sugar slowly and add the vanilla.
Fold in nuts and crackers.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour and the sugar.
In heavy saucepan, combine butter, shortening, coffee or water and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over the flour and sugar in the bowl.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well, using a wooden spoon or high speed on electric mixer.
Pour into a well buttered 17 1/2 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brownies test done in the center.
Frost as soon as you take brownies out of the oven.
Cool and cut into 48 bars.

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Place margarine in pan and melt in oven.
Keep oven hot at 325°.
Combine sugar, milk and flour in a bowl.
Stir until smooth. Add strawberries.
Place all ingredients in pan with melted margarine and bake for approximately 1 hour or until golden brown. Make sure middle is not soggy.
If it is, cook for 10 more minutes.

title: golden pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops and brown in frying pan.
Set aside and drain any grease from pan.
Combine mushroom soup, onion, wine and water in frying pan and heat until smooth.
Stir often.
Add pork chops and cover.
Let simmer over medium heat for about 45 minutes.

title: yummy popsicles
directions: Mix juice with yogurt.
Add vanilla and sweeten to taste. Pour into ice cube trays and stand half of a popsicle stick in each cube section.
Freeze.
Remove from trays and place in freezer bags for easy access.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours. Great vegetable dip.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Melt butter in skillet or pan.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Return batter to skillet or pan and bake at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: old fashioned bread stuffing
directions: Cook and stir onion and celery in margarine in medium skillet over medium heat until tender.
Stir in seasonings.
Add onion mixture and chicken broth to bread in large bowl.
Toss to mix; stuff turkey
or bake separate as a side dish.
Makes 8 cups, enough to stuff 12 to 14 pound turkey.

title: matzas balls
directions: Beat whites until stiff.
Beat in yolks. Fold in matzo meal and salt.
Let stand 15 minutes or more.
Form into balls with wet hands and drop into boiling water or soup.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into mixing bowl. Combine milk and salad oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Drop from tablespoon atop bubbling stew.
Cover; return to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 10 servings.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Fold into oil mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add prunes, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan or greased tube pan at 350° until done.

title: corn chowder
directions: Add salt and freshly ground white pepper, to taste.

title: always tender squirrel
directions: Cut squirrels into serving size pieces and salt and pepper each piece, then roll in flour.
Heat some cooking oil in a large frying pan and brown the squirrels on both sides.
Put squirrel into crock-pot.
Add soup, water, onions and mushrooms.
Turn crock-pot to high for 1/2 hour, then turn heat to low and add sour cream and cook for 6 hours.
The gravy can be thinned with water or thickened with flour and is excellent over mashed potatoes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: diabetic fruitcake
directions: Mix together butter and sweeteners.
Add egg.
Add flour and vanilla; mix well.
Add dates, raisins and pecans; mix well.
Pour into miniature baking pans.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Into a 2 quart casserole crush crackers and mix with oleo.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Boil giblets until tender. Save stock.
Chop giblets and set aside.
In frypan melt margarine.
Add flour, stirring, but do not brown.
When well mixed add stock, stirring until smooth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add giblets and chopped eggs.
Add more stock as needed.

title: granny wilson's chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil to thicken. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat until slightly cooled and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: pasta salad
directions: In a large container with lid, add all of the ingredients. Place lid on container and shake.
Refrigerate for 1 hour to distribute flavor.
Shake or stir before serving.

title: machaca
directions: Do not trim brisket; wrap in foil and cook in oven at 350° until well done enough to fall apart.
