Then trim brisket and shred with two forks.
Pour salsa over meat and let it soak in.
Heat before serving.
Fold in flour tortillas and top with sour cream and avocado pieces.
Brisket freezes well for later use.

title: pickled red beets
directions: Boil beets until tender.
Remove skins.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag.
Heat vinegar, water, sugar and spices to boiling point.
Add beets and boil 5 minutes.
Pack in sterile jars; fill with hot liquid and seal.

title: high octane energy bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.
Toast the first three ingredients in a 350° preheated oven for about 10 minutes, stirring once after 5 minutes (do not let mixture brown).
Move mixture to a large mixing bowl.
Add apricots, raisins, wheat germ and protein powder, separating the dried fruit so they don't stick together and mixing all ingredients thoroughly.
In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter and add brown rice syrup, stirring until bubbly.
Mix in the last two ingredients.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill until time for serving. This sauce will keep well in refrigerator for as much as 4 or 5 days if stored in tightly sealed jar.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Mix macaroni and remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Spoon in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Roll
meat
in mixture of 4 tablespoons of flour, salt, pepper and
garlic.
Brown
in
oil.
Add
onions.
Cook for 4 minutes. Remove
meat.
Add
2 tablespoons of oil and brown 2 tablespoons of
flour
in
it.
Slowly add 4 cups of water and mix until thickened.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, meat, bay leaf and celery seed. Cover
and
simmer
for 2 hours.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, carrots and potatoes.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Add peas and parsley.

title: layered dip
directions: Put on a large plate with rim.
For the first layer, spread the refried beans.
For second layer, mash the avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
For third layer, mix the sour cream with the mayonnaise and package of taco seasoning.
For fourth layer, layer the chopped green onions, tomatoes, olives and shredded cheese one at a time over the top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into chocolate cookie crust; refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: braised cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers, remove seeds and dice.
Have the celery diced in about the same size pieces.
Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add onion, cucumbers, celery and a sprinkling of salt and pepper.
A teaspoon of dried dill weed adds immeasurably to the flavor of this dish.
Cook gently, turning so that the vegetables become golden on all sides.
Add water; cover tightly and simmer until tender, not more than about 10 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes; cool slightly.
Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out potato, being careful not to tear skins.
Mash with milk to moisten.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mash together.
Mound in shells and place in shallow pan.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°, or until heated through.

title: caramels
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add corn syrup and sugar.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Rub into meat well.
Melt butter in skillet, then brown meat in it.
Add vegetables and water. Cover and simmer slowly for 2 hours.

title: jello fruit delite
directions: Mix dry Jell-O and sour cream. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Pour in Pyrex dish. Decorate top with fruit.

title: red salsa with baked chips
directions: Put chopped onion and garlic in strainer and pour 2 cups boiling water over them; drain thoroughly.
Discard water and cool completely.
Peel tomatoes, remove seeds and chop.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate to allow flavors to blend.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms quickly, dry immediately.
Mix remaining ingredients together, add to the mushrooms, toss until all pieces are very well coated.
Let stand at room temperature at least 4 hours.
The mushrooms are never cooked.

title: glorified rice
directions: 1 c. rice, cooked well done.
Let stand until cool, then add 1 c milk and let cool until dry.
Then add 1 c. sugar, 1 big can crushed pineapple, drained, 1/4 pound marshmallows, 1/2 pint cream, whipped stiff, maraschino cherries and red cake coloring.
Let stand over night.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook milk, sugar and rice until it's sort of thick.
Take off heat.
Beat in beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add raisins and pour into pan or bowl.
It will thicken as it cools.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: lasagne
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet, add ground beef and garlic.
Brown in oil.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Cook noodles in rapidly boiling salted water about 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Fill a casserole or loaf pan with alternate layers of noodles, cheese, tomato-meat sauce and Parmesan cheese, ending with a layer of tomato-meat sauce and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until it is firm.
Serves 4.

title: lynn's baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger and drain well.
Put hamburger in crock pot and mix together with rest of ingredients.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Drain and keep juice from cherries and pineapple.
Add water to make 2 cups.
Heat juices and water to boiling.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add cola and fruits to gelatin mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart dish or mold.
Chill until set. (Delicious and always brings compliments.)

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: Put peppers, cut up, in blender and shred with vinegar.
Blend well.
Add sugar.
Cook slowly to rolling boil.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Skim.
Add Certo and coloring.
Return to just boiling, boil for 1 minute and put in sterile jars.
Add paraffin to seal. Serve with crackers over cream cheese.
Good with scrambled eggs or lamb.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
In a 12 x 10 x 2-inch casserole dish, cut up chicken in chunks.
Drain all cans with liquid in them. Pour all ingredients in dish and mix well.
Grate your choice of cheese over the top of casserole.
Preheat oven to 325° and cook for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice (optional).

title: leftover cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift baking powder, soda and salt with flour.
Add flour mixture and sour cream alternately using flour mixture first and last.
Stir in raisins and pecans.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight. Grease cookie sheet.
Drop by teaspoon or roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes (no more than this).
Ice with Browned Butter Icing.

title: coconut cake with pineapple and whipped cream
directions: Punch holes in cake and spread Eagle Brand milk on top; let cool. Mix remaining ingredients and spread on cake.
Refrigerate. (Better second day.)

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream together well the Crisco, butter or margarine and white sugar.
Add egg and milk.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, baking powder soda and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture.
Add into mixture the raisins and walnuts (optional).
Chill a bit before forming into cookies.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 200 cookies.

title: aunt mat's apple pie
directions: Combine sugar and butter; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Peel and slice enough apples to fill crust.

title: old-fashioned stack cake
directions: Use 9-inch cake pans and lightly grease pans.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and ginger.
Cream shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla at high speed.
Reduce speed and blend in molasses and buttermilk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Divide into 5 parts and roll each out in thickness of pie crust.
Makes 5 layers. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
After they have cooled, put cooked, dried apples in between each layer.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with chips and cheese.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: friendship bread
directions: Mix well and pour into greased pans and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes (until center springs up when you press it like a cake).

title: chicken puffs
directions: Fry chicken breasts in pan.
Season with salt, oregano and a little pepper.
When done, remove from pan and cool.
Take meat off bones.
Roll out patty shells (tart side up) and fill each with chicken and 1 slice Mozzarella cheese.
Put on ungreased pan and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until golden.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add scallions and 3/4 of the beef cut into small pieces. Add a little salt and a few drops of Worcestershire sauce. Add mayonnaise.
Mix together and chill for several hours. Cut up remaining beef.
Form cream cheese mixture into ball. Roll it in the remaining beef.

title: fried corn
directions: Clean and cut corn into a large bowl and put to side.
In large iron skillet, brown bacon.
Remove from skillet and put to the side.
Put corn in skillet; salt and pepper to taste in oil from bacon.
Let cook for about 15 minutes, covered.
Remove lid; add 3 tablespoons flour in 1 cup of water.
Mix well and pour into corn.
Stir often.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add sugar to taste and butter.

title: doris' sugarless apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice.
Add apples for 4 minutes.
Remove slices from juice.
Add spices to the juices and thicken with cornstarch mixture.
Place apples, unbaked, in pie shell and pour thickened juice on top.
Add top crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan or a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Melt margarine and stir in brown sugar.
Cool 10 minutes.
Then add eggs to the brown sugar mixture one at a time.
Stir in flour mixture, nuts and chocolate chips until well blended.
Spread into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until light brown.
Don't overcook or they will become hard after cooled.

title: dream pie
directions: Combine pie filling, sugar, crushed pineapple and cornstarch and cook until thick.
Add orange jello and let stand 30 minutes, then add bananas and pecans.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes. Cook in boiling water 15 minutes. Remove from heat. Cool and peel.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Place butter, corn syrup, water and sugar in heavy skillet.
Arrange potatoes on top, cut side down.
Cook over very low heat, basting occasionally, about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and well glazed.

title: new england corn chowder
directions: In a large soup pot, fry the bacon until crispy.
Drain most, but not all, of the grease.
Add the cubed potatoes and onion. Cover over with water, being careful not to add too much water. Cook until potatoes are soft.
Add the evaporated milk and the four cans of corn to the hot mixture.
Stir and add about 2 to 3 cups of milk.
Simmer over a low heat for 1 hour.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Bone thighs. Cut into pieces.
Saute in oil in pan. Simmer for 30 minutes (adding bay leaf the last 2 minutes).
Remove chicken from pan. Saute pepper and onion slices in oil for 15 minutes. Remove.
Mix garlic, tomatoes and mushrooms. Cook for 15 minutes. Add everything back to pan. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: kolaches
directions: Mix sugar and shortening to milk; stir, then add cool water. Add yeast, which has stood in warm water for 5 minutes.
Add egg and flour; beat.
Let rise until double in size.
Knead down and then make Kolaches.
Let rise a few minutes before adding fruit. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Use any kind of fruit.
When slightly cooled, drizzle with powdered sugar, mixed with a little milk or cream.

title: light biscuits
directions: Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 1 hour.
Contains 220 calories per cup.

title: jackie's ham delight
directions: Place pineapple on top of ham.
Put ham in crock-pot and all ingredients.
Mix brown sugar and pineapple juice in a cup and add to the pot.
Slow cook 3 to 4 hours, or it may be baked at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve juice over rice.

title: oriental chicken wings(makes 16 - easily doubles and triples)
directions: Blend soy sauce, sugar, oil, ginger and garlic powder in a large bowl until sugar dissolves.
Stir in green onions.
Add chicken wings to marinade, turning to coat.
Cover chicken and refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: In a saucepan, combine flour, pineapple juice, orange juice concentrate, sugar, honey and lemon juice. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly. Cool. Serve desired amount over cut up fruit.

title: seven day sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours and drain.
Repeat each day for 4 days, using fresh water each time.
On fifth day, cut cucumbers in rings.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Bring liquid to a boil and pour over sliced cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain syrup and bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Repeat on sixth day.
On last day, drain off syrup again and bring it to a boil, add cucumbers slices, bring to boiling point.
Can.

title: sausage breakfast pizza
directions: You will need a pizza pan (spray with Pam).

title: baked lemon chicken oregano
directions: Wash chicken.
Heat butter and oil together.
Pour half of it into a shallow baking pan.
Spread to cover bottom.
Lay chicken in pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and oregano.
Mix remaining butter mixture with lemon juice.
Baste chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°, basting at 3 or 4 times during baking.
Add boiling water to drippings in pan; mix.
Dilute flour or cornstarch in 1/2 cup cold water and stir into pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 475°.
Serve separately as sauce for mashed potatoes or rice pilaf.
May boil potatoes or rice and bake with chicken for 1/2 hour.

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Cook instant rice as directed on package.
Saute onion in margarine. Add all other ingredients which have already been combined.
Mix lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes in a greased casserole.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except eggs.
Pour into large buttered casserole dish.
Fold in eggs.
Cover lightly.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, uncover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice with pine nuts
directions: Saute onions in butter for 1 minute.
Add rice and consomme. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
After cooking, add pine nuts and parsley.
Season to taste.

title: sour cream chocolate pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat sour cream and milk together until smooth. Gradually add pudding and beat until thoroughly combined and slightly thickened.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups La Creme into chocolate mixture.
Pour filling into graham shell.
Top with remaining La Creme. Chill until firm, about 2 to 3 hours.
If desired, sprinkle with chocolate curls.
Serves 6.

title: health bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together in medium bowl.
Stir well and turn batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix Bisquick with flour and add milk; mix.
Knead on floured surface 10 to 12 times.
Roll or pat out until you have a 1/2-inch thick rectangle (8 x 12-inches).
Cover with meat and season to taste.
Roll into a log.
Cut 1/2-inch slices and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes.
(Can add cheese during last 2 minutes.)
Serve with gravy, if desired.

title: light fruitcake
directions: Combine nuts, cherries, pineapple and raisins.
Toss with the 1 cup flour; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until light and add eggs.
Stir in lemon.
In separate bowl, sift together flour and baking powder.
Add to wet mixture in thirds, mixing well after each.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan.
Cover tightly with foil. Place a pan of hot water on bottom rack of oven.
Bake cake on rack above water in slow oven at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove foil.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes more until top is slightly dry.
Remove cake from pan when cooled.
Store in tightly covered container. Before serving, brush with light corn syrup.
Garnish with candied cherries.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Butter baking dish.
Pour apple pie filling.
Mix Bisquick, sugar, egg, butter and spices.
Spoon over pie filling.
Top with pecans.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Cut tomatoes; cover with lime and water.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Rinse lime off real well.
Put salt over tomatoes and cover with cold water.
Let stand while you cut up other ingredients.

title: best chops in the west
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet. Brown chops on both sides. Saute garlic. Combine 2 teaspoons oil, sherry or broth, soy sauce, brown sugar and red pepper. Place chops in skillet. Pour sauce over them. Cover and simmer until chops are tender 30 to 35 minutes. Add a little water if needed. Turn once. Remove chops to platter. Stir in cornstarch to skillet until thickened. Pour over chops and serve.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast.
Add sugar, salt and half the flour.
Beat thoroughly and add eggs and shortening.
Work in remaining flour until smooth.
Place in bowl; cover with damp cloth and waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally.
Shape in rolls 2 hours before baking.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400°.
(Makes 4 dozen.)

title: crepes
directions: Put milk in blender.
Crack open and drop eggs into blender with butter.
Turn blender on medium.
Slowly shake flour into blender while blending.
Sprinkle in salt.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in pan.
Pour mixture of all ingredients in. Spoon oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter creme easter eggs
directions: Mix margarine, cream cheese and sugar well and form into egg shapes.
Refrigerate to harden.
Heat chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Put onto eggs and keep refrigerated.

title: mrs. bihrs' peanut fudge
directions: Cook sugar, peanut butter and milk in saucepan to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Pour into a buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: hot dip
directions: Chop artichokes medium fine.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: crusty beef, cheese and noodle casserole
directions: Heat oil; add onions and cook until golden.
Add meat and cook until meat loses its red color.
Add spaghetti sauce and salt. Heat.
Arrange in casserole half the noodles, half sauce and half cheese.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt.
Make another layer and top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: oven baked meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together. With wet hands, shape meat into 1-inch balls. Place in two 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pans. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Place meatballs on another baking pan to cool. Place in freezer just until frozen. Seal in plastic bags and freeze.

title: breakfast biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together into medium bowl. Work in shortening while adding milk until all ingredients are formed into a smooth ball.
Dust hands with flour, if needed, to help shape dough.
Turn out onto floured board.
Pat out to desired thickness (biscuits double in size when baked).
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Mix vegetables with sauerkraut.
Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Pour over vegetables; cool for 24 hours before serving.
May freeze after 4 to 5 days.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in 1 cup water and juice from the pineapple.
If green pepper is used, cook this with the chicken. Do not let the chicken cook on.
Add more water if necessary and if there seems to be more liquid than you'd like, thicken with 1 tablespoon cornstarch or flour mixed with cold water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; add onion and continue to brown. Cook macaroni; add all ingredients except onion and hamburger mixture to cooked macaroni.
Layer hamburger and macaroni mixture. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 345°.

title: lemon refrigerator pie
directions: Blend
condensed milk, lemon juice, egg yolks and lemon extract.
Mixture will thicken as blended.

title: blackberry grape jelly
directions: Combine juices in a sauce pan; add sure-gel fruit pectin. Bring mixture to a rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Quickly add sugar, bring to full rolling boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Put in jars. Invert jars for 5 minutes and turn right side up.

title: peach salad
directions: Combine gelatin and sugar; stir in the 2 cups orange juice and peel.
Heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat; cool to room temperature.
Stir in buttermilk.
Chill until partially set. Fold in fruit.
Turn into a 6 1/2-cup mold.
Chill until firm. For dressing, stir together sour cream and 1/4 cup orange juice. Cover and chill.
To serve, unmold salad onto lettuce lined platter; pass dressing.
Serves 10.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecan halves.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells.
Cover with pecan halves.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Sift and set aside flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Cream butter, oil and sugar on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Blend together vanilla and buttermilk and add alternately with dry ingredients to egg and sugar mixture.
Stir in grated zucchini.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut in squares.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Combine first four ingredients together.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl
add
buttermilk.
Dip
chicken
pieces
into buttermilk and then into batter.
Place into a foil lined cake pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake
at
for 45 minutes. Remove from oven; uncover.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake an additional 15 minutes at 425°, uncovered.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll into a ball and roll in 1 1/2 cups finely chopped pecans.

title: mexican casserole(microwave)
directions: In a large pan, cook the beef, green pepper and onion.
Drain fat.
Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce and paste, olives, water and chili powder.
Microwave at High until thickened, about 8 minutes.
Blend sour cream and eggs in a small bowl.

title: apple cookies
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add next 7 ingredients. Mix together and add the last 3 ingredients.
Drop dough and bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: pineapple supreme cake
directions: Pour juice from
crushed
pineapple
into pudding.
Mix well. Don't add anything else to pudding.
Add Cool Whip into crushed pineapple, then
add
this	mixture into cream cheese. (Cream cheese should
be
softened.) Prepare cake according to directions on box.
Cut
cake
into
layers;
add	topping between layers and over cake.

title: strawberry-banana shake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix.

title: in-a-pinch pudding
directions: *It's easy to skimp on the powdered sugar or sour cream; anything in a pinch.

title: mirabella's chicken, broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix together soup, oleo, cheese and broth.
Warm a little and pour over rice, broccoli and chicken.
Cover with Cheese Nips crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach.
Discard stems; tear into bite sized pieces. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Combine oil and garlic in a bowl; let stand for 2 hours.
Discard oil.

title: hoppin' john
directions: In skillet cook bacon until crisp.
Drain away fat but 1 tablespoonful.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is done.

title: microwave fast fixin chocolate fudge
directions: In
large
bowl,
mix
sugar
and
cocoa.
Add milk and butter (do
not
stir).
Heat 4 1/2 to 6 minutes on High until butter is melted; add nuts and vanilla, stirring until smooth. Spread into well-greased square baking dish; chill until firm. Cut into squares to serve.
Yields about 3 pounds.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Brown bacon and onion in skillet until onion is tender.
Add cabbage and carrots, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 10 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the shortening, brown sugar, egg, molasses, flour, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon and ginger; mix well.
I also add nuts and chocolate.
Roll dough into balls using 1 teaspoon of dough.
Place balls on greased baking sheet. Flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in white sugar.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 8 minutes or until done.

title: double apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine both flours, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
In a blender container, combine applesauce, egg, oil, vanilla and sweetener.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in apples (I sometimes add raisins and pecans).
Add applesauce mixture to dry ingredients. Mix until all ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 8 muffin cups that have been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray (sometimes I use mini muffin pans).
Bake 20 to 22 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the center of muffin comes out clean. Remove to rack to cool.
Delicious hot or cold.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat fat in Dutch oven.
Add onions and pepper.
Saute.
Add meat and cook until brown, stirring to separate meat.
Pour tomatoes and soup into blender.
Blend until liquid and add to meat mixture.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer about one hour, stirring occasionally.
Add water if mixture gets too thick. Combine garlic and salt; add with beans to meat mixture.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Freeze leftovers.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt oleo in a saucepan; add eggs and milk.
Then add flour, cocoa and sugar together.
Add this to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash and clean mushrooms.
Slice red onion thin and break into rings.
Put layer of mushrooms, onion and spices; repeat. Sprinkle sugar.
Add oil and vinegar.
Let set 3 days in refrigerator.
Do not use metal container.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Cook on top of stove.
Melt margarine in skillet and add onion and celery.
Cook until glazed, but not browned.
Add ground beef and garlic salt and simmer until done.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese warm to room temperature.
Mix cheese, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour into a graham cracker pie shell.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Top with pie filling.

title: dirt cake
directions: Soften cream cheese and oleo. Mix in Cool Whip and powdered sugar. Set aside. In a separate bowl, take the pudding and make as directed on box. Then add to mixture. Put 1/2 of the crushed cookies in 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour on top of mixture. Freeze. Serve frozen. Tastes like ice cream sandwich.

title: different chicken casserole
directions: Put
bacon
in	bottom	of
Pyrex dish.
Add rice, then chicken.
Mix soup with 2/3 cup water; put in spices.
Mix and pour over
chicken.
Cover.
Bake
in
350° oven for 1 hour or longer, if needed, for chicken to be done.

title: scrambled zucchini and eggs
directions: Pan-fry zucchini in butter until tender; add eggs, milk and pepper.
Scramble until mixture is dry.
Add cheese and cook until it is melted.

title: southern peanut butter pie
directions: Chill the pie crust.
Beat eggs.
Add corn syrup, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir in peanuts. Pour filling into chilled shell; bake for 15 minutes in a 400° preheated oven.
Turn heat down to 350° and bake for
30 or 35 minutes.
Let cool.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix together and serve on individual plates with a lettuce leaf.

title: patio salad
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in a jar; shake until well mixed. Set aside.
In covered bowl, mix mushrooms, parsley, onion and kielbasa.
Top with dressing.
Stir all together and chill several hours.
Can be served on lettuce.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: *Use less sugar, if you don't want it as sweet.

title: forty-niners
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, biscuit mix and pecans; blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven and cool thoroughly.
Cut into bars and dust with powdered sugar.
Yields 48 squares.

title: pepper corn
directions: Cut corn from cob, milk cobs.
Melt margarine in saucepan. Add all peppers.
Saute 3 to 4 minutes on medium.
Add corn and cook only 5 or 6 minutes.
Add salt to taste.
Great side dish with cookout meals.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in the water until water is gone.
Add applesauce, cooking and mix well.
Blend soda and flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Bring to boil and add can of evaporated milk.
Boil 4 or 5 minutes until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce and water.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add tortilla chips to mixture. Serve.

title: old fashioned muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a bowl, combine dry ingredients. Mix well.
Blend in butter and shortening with pastry blender. Combine milk, vanilla and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients, all at once. Stir until barely moistened.
Do not overmix.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins containing 200 calories each.

title: low-fat oatmeal muffins(cholesterol lowering)
directions: Run oat bran through food processor a few minutes to make more like flour consistency.
Combine dry ingredients; combine liquids and add to the dry ingredients.
Add raisins or nuts.
Mix until just moistened.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: michael and marissa's fruit dip
directions: In mixing bowl or blender beat together cream cheese and marshmallow until smooth.
Sprinkle cut up fruit with Fruit Fresh or lemon juice to prevent browning.
Serve on platter with dip in middle.
Garnish platter as desired.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Sugar-free, reduced calorie pudding and Cool Whip may be substituted.

title: sandy's cheese ball
directions: Chop up beef.
Mix with other ingredients, saving some of the beef.
After well mixed, form into ball.
Use the rest of the beef to cover the outside of the ball or roll the ball in the chopped nuts.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and ham. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle cheese and ham on top. Push below surface with fork. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Check after 35 minutes. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in casserole dish.
Mix together mushroom soup, onion, cheese, egg and mayonnaise.
Pour over top of broccoli.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Pour melted margarine in cracker crumbs and mix well.
Spread crumbs on top and bake until brown.

title: golden parsley potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, Cheddar and onions in casserole dish.
In blender, mix cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and parsley.
Pour this over the potatoes. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with fresh parsley.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line jelly roll pan with crackers.
Melt margarine and butter. Add sugar; bring to a rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers in pan.
Spread to cover all crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Allow to cool slightly (10 to 15 seconds).
Remove bars from pan and place on foil.
Allow to cool completely.

title: low country boil
directions: In large pot, mix a gallon of water with the liquid crab boil and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add corn and boil for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and boil for 10 minutes.
Add onions and sausage and boil for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp.
After 5 minutes, drain and serve with crusty bread.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dill dip(low-fat)
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: lazy beef stew
directions: Cover with water and bake 3 hours at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: whiskey sour punch
directions: Prepare garnish.
Thinly slice orange. Discard ends. With small sharp knife, flute edges of slices. Set aside.
In punch bowl, combine undiluted lemonade, concentrate and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Garnish with orange slices.
Makes 16 cups or 32 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into balls. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender, then drain. Arrange on bottom of greased 11 x 7-inch or 11 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put chicken on top, then combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Saute onion and drain.
Mix drained veggies with onion and Cheez Whiz.
Place in casserole dish sprayed with cooking spray (Pam).
Crush Ritz crackers.
Mix with 1 stick melted butter. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's cheese macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain.
Spray baking dish with nonstick spray.
Mix hot macaroni with cheese and stir.
Add 1 egg (slightly beaten) and 2 large cans of evaporated milk and pour into baking dish.
Cut butter into small pats and place on top. Bake at 450° for approximately 15 minutes only until set.
This will make a very creamy cheese macaroni after it sets for a few minutes.

title: breakfast sausage pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls in the bottom of a 9 x 11-inch cake pan. Press edges together. Brown and drain sausage.
Put on top of crescent rolls.
Beat eggs with a little salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage.
Add cheese on top of mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage kolache
directions: Mix sugar, oil, salt and hot milk in large bowl.
When cooled to lukewarm, add beaten egg and yeast (dissolved in warm water). Add flour until dough is soft, but no longer sticky.
Knead on floured board; dough should be soft, not sticky.
Put dough in clean, lightly oiled bowl; cover with damp cloth and let rise in a warm place until double in size (about 1 1/2 hours).
Turn out on board.
Cut into 32 pieces.
Flatten each piece and roll around a sausage.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise about 1 hour or until double.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: olive spaghetti with italian meat sauce
directions: In a skillet, brown beef; add onion and garlic and cook until transparent; drain.
Stir in tomato paste, water, seasonings and mushrooms.
Simmer uncovered 15 to 20 minutes, or until sauce reaches desired consistency; stir occasionally.
On heated serving platter, toss hot spaghetti with olives; pour sauce over.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: fried cabbage and pasta with sausage
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
In large skillet (electric frypan works well) cook cabbage and onions in 4 tablespoons margarine for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add cooked noodles and remaining margarine.
Mix well.
Place sausage on top of mixture. Cover and cook over low heat 15 to 20 minutes or until sausage is hot and flavors are blended.
Makes 5 servings.

title: striped delight
directions: *Or use 1 package (6 ounce serving) instant pudding and 2 1/2 cups cold milk.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Debone chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix all (except cheese) in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle with cheese on top.
Return to oven and bake 15 more minutes.

title: garlic croutons
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, heat olive oil and butter until melted, then add parsley and garlic. Toss bread cubes in oil mixture. Bake at 200°, stirring every 10 minutes, until toasted, but not crunchy (about 40 to 50 minutes). Excellent with any Italian type salad. Store in the refrigerator in a Ziploc baggie.
